1
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,790
What's with this island?

2
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:24,670
Oh, no! They started shooting already!

3
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:49,630
Duck!

4
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:52,260
Oh, crap!

5
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,070
<i>I have a plan!</i>

6
00:00:59,190 --> 00:01:02,740
<i>Which will kill Straw Hat Luffy!</i>

7
00:01:03,340 --> 00:01:08,790
<i>And which will exterminate the Straw Hats!</i>

8
00:01:09,630 --> 00:01:15,570
I think you all remember the day
Straw Hat rampaged through the Navy HQ.

9
00:01:16,150 --> 00:01:20,890
That was certainly an incident
that symbolized the Great Pirate Era.

10
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:24,920
Once again, make sure to engrave the faces of the enemies

11
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:27,030
that disturb our peace into your minds!

12
00:01:27,540 --> 00:01:30,190
The swordsman, "Pirate Hunter" Zoro!

13
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:35,880
The navigator, "Cat Burglar" Nami!

14
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:42,210
The sniper, "King of Snipers" Sniper King!

15
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:47,020
The cook, "Black-Foot" Sanji!

16
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:52,360
Whoa! You surprised me!

17
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,380
I just felt somebody laughing at me!

18
00:01:55,070 --> 00:01:58,090
The archeologist, "Demon Child" Nico Robin!

19
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:02,100
The shipwright, "Cyborg" Franky!

20
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:06,100
The musician, "Humming Swordsman" Brook!

21
00:02:07,290 --> 00:02:10,350
The ship doctor,
"Cotton Candy Lover" Chopper!

22
00:02:12,380 --> 00:02:16,720
Lastly, although he's a pirate,
he's Vice Admiral Garp's grandson!

23
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:19,180
The Revolutionary Dragon's son!

24
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:24,160
The captain, "Straw Hat" Luffy!

25
00:02:26,770 --> 00:02:29,480
Those nine are our enemies!

26
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:32,900
I have a plan! I see a chance for victory!

27
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:36,130
"Straw Hat Destruction Maneuver."

28
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:39,240
STRAW HAT DESTRUCTION MANEUVER

29
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,240
Commence!

30
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,480
Yes, sir!

31
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:46,540
ADVENTURE OF NEBULANDIA

32
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,750
I'm hungry!

33
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:51,880
Sanji! Food!

34
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:55,710
<i>Meat! Meat! No vegetables!</i>

35
00:02:55,710 --> 00:02:58,670
You're so damn annoying!
Wait a minute!

36
00:02:58,670 --> 00:03:01,490
<i>Hungry! Hungry! I'm hungry!</i>

37
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:13,000
Found one! I found a coconut!

38
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,090
Let me see.

39
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:19,170
How did you find it?!

40
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:22,360
It's a nice distance.

41
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:24,870
All right!

42
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:35,150
Usopp-<i>san</i> won!

43
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,170
Yes!

44
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:38,510
Damn! I won't lose the next one!

45
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:39,360
Okay!

46
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,010
Oh, no...

47
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,110
Thanks!

48
00:03:44,220 --> 00:03:46,930
Franky! You've lost three in a row!

49
00:03:46,930 --> 00:03:48,350
Shut up!

50
00:03:48,350 --> 00:03:51,350
Why are you two betting
without asking! Boy!

51
00:03:51,350 --> 00:03:53,270
Oh, an empty bottle this time!

52
00:03:53,270 --> 00:03:55,310
Great! I'll get it again!

53
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:56,920
That's my line!

54
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,070
Where is it?

55
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:02,860
It's in the direction of that
odd-shaped island. Oh?

56
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,120
What's wrong?

57
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:08,290
I see something blinking. A signal?

58
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:10,430
--What's the matter?
--A signal?

59
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:15,350
That's an SOS.

60
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,040
Huh? What?

61
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:19,480
Seems like there's a distress signal
from the island.

62
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:24,430
What's with the island?!
There are a bunch of mushrooms!

63
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:26,680
Can I eat them?

64
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,860
You're so quick!

65
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:31,490
Does it mean somebody's there? Who is it?

66
00:04:31,930 --> 00:04:32,910
Wait a sec.

67
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,900
There's a ship. It's stranded.

68
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:39,220
A crowd on the beach...

69
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,920
They're all women!

70
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,590
--Oh?!
--Women!

71
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:45,860
Sanji! Weren't you cooking meat?

72
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:46,790
Here you go.

73
00:04:48,490 --> 00:04:50,470
Anyway, what should we do?

74
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:53,230
What should we do? Of course, we...

75
00:04:53,570 --> 00:04:56,210
...as decent humans, can't turn our backs!

76
00:04:56,210 --> 00:04:57,810
Sanji! You're bleeding from your nose.

77
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:00,130
So we're gonna stop by the island?

78
00:05:00,130 --> 00:05:02,570
Well, we have no choice.

79
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:04,700
Wait, wait!

80
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:09,210
How could you decide it without asking us!
What if it messes up the Log Pose?

81
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:13,270
I can just repair their ship quickly
before it gathers too many logs.

82
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:17,250
Alright. It's fine, then.
But make sure to charge them for the repair.

83
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:20,090
--You're...
--That's my Nami!

84
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:22,990
What do you say, Captain?

85
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:26,570
No problem! The island looks delicious.

86
00:05:26,570 --> 00:05:30,780
Nami-<i>san</i>! Starboard helm and full speed!

87
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:31,850
Alright, alright.

88
00:05:31,950 --> 00:05:37,520
Ladies, wait there!
Your knight is on his way!

89
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,420
I'm the one who'll repair the ship!

90
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:41,310
I hope I can eat some mushrooms.

91
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:52,060
It's a beautiful island!

92
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:56,770
It's normally deserted.
Nature remains untouched here.

93
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:05,780
Hey, are you all right?

94
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:09,530
We received your SOS signal!

95
00:06:09,530 --> 00:06:14,430
I'm a shipwright!
I'll repair your ship so hold on!

96
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:17,620
It's a big mushroom! Yum-yum!

97
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:21,750
Don't eat it!
Until I find out if it's edible or not.

98
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:24,050
I'm practically immune to poison!

99
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:29,080
I said don't! There are some poisons
that'll cause changes to your body!

100
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:35,020
They're really all women!

101
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:38,410
Is anybody hurt? I'm a doctor!

102
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:44,280
That ship...
I think I remember it from somewhere...

103
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:47,420
And the memories are bad...

104
00:06:48,210 --> 00:06:50,820
You're in good hands now, girls!

105
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:53,600
My <i>nouvelle cuisine</i> will help you!

106
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:58,730
Boy, I'll leave them behind
if the Log Pose starts to get affected.

107
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:14,280
Some of those people aren't women!

108
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,930
Huh? Looks like they're all women to me!

109
00:07:16,930 --> 00:07:20,230
Only the ones up front are women!
Behind them are...

110
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:25,610
That's what I'd expect from
Black-Foot the woman chaser!

111
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:26,840
Who are you?!

112
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:32,000
It's been a while, Straw Hats!

113
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:36,120
I wanted to see you guys
so I looked and looked and...

114
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,270
...looked all over for you!

115
00:07:38,290 --> 00:07:40,790
What's with that big-headed woman?

116
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:43,690
Chopper?

117
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:46,960
--Oh!
--Why is he here in the New World?!

118
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:50,940
Yes, it's me!
The captain of the Foxy Pirates,

119
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:55,550
"Silver Fox" Foxy-<i>sama</i>!

120
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,590
Ooh!

121
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:12,530
Everyone, remove your make-up!

122
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:18,020
We came to avenge ourselves on you
for humiliating us!

123
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:23,310
Can't speak from astonishment?

124
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:25,310
Wait, who are you?

125
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:27,880
He doesn't remember me...

126
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,190
Boss!

127
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:34,720
Oh no, Boss, cheer up!
How dare you pretend that you don't remember!

128
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:36,680
No, I really don't know.

129
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,870
Hey, Hamburg! It's not funny!

130
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:43,560
Do you know him?

131
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:49,570
Ah, he's from that thing.
The Davy Back Fight. Remember?

132
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:52,260
Davy... Oh!

133
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:55,570
We did the pirate game
before we got to Water Seven!

134
00:08:55,570 --> 00:08:57,660
Now you remember?! You dullard!

135
00:08:57,660 --> 00:09:00,720
Yeah, I remember!
If I'm correct, your name is...

136
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:02,520
...Split-Head Fox-taro!

137
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,690
Okay! You got it all wrong!

138
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:09,420
It's been a long time!
I'm glad that you're doing fine... Um...

139
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:14,400
I'm Foxy! Don't forget!
We fought so fiercely!

140
00:09:15,470 --> 00:09:19,680
This time we're being treated to
a captain-versus-captain battle!

141
00:09:20,650 --> 00:09:23,250
Silver Fox Foxy!

142
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,870
Straw Hat Luffy!

143
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,540
I'm... the real deal!

144
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:33,090
It's dragging me away!

145
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:35,170
Dear me! Whatever's the matter?

146
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:48,500
That's already settled!

147
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,840
Yeah, you're right! Damn right!

148
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:56,400
But I can't just let it go
since you stopped my undefeated streak!

149
00:09:56,910 --> 00:10:02,260
We're totally different from
the Foxy Pirates we used to be!

150
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:04,060
Your head got split even more?

151
00:10:04,060 --> 00:10:05,910
Uh-huh... No way!

152
00:10:05,930 --> 00:10:07,060
Boss!

153
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:12,250
Screw you!
You fooled me with crap like that?!

154
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:16,820
We learned about your personality inside and out
in the last battle.

155
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:20,700
We thought it'd be a piece of cake
with our beautiful ladies.

156
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:21,960
It's called...

157
00:10:21,490 --> 00:10:25,120
BEAUTIFUL LADY MANIPULATION MANEUVER

158
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:24,600
..."Beautiful Lady Manipulation Maneuver"!

159
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:29,420
Because you're an idiot,
it went exactly as we planned.

160
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,690
Shut up!

161
00:10:30,830 --> 00:10:33,130
I see! It was an incredible plan!

162
00:10:33,130 --> 00:10:34,840
Hey, Usopp, you fool!

163
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,380
Sanji!

164
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:38,510
All right! It's my bad!

165
00:10:38,510 --> 00:10:43,330
But was it worth wrecking your ship?

166
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:49,710
I already told you.
We're different from the way we used to be.

167
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:52,110
--Dojaku!
--Okay, Boss!

168
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:58,590
The all-new Foxy Pirates!
Show them the brand-new Foxy that suits us!

169
00:10:58,590 --> 00:10:59,660
Got it!

170
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:41,620
It's completely transformed!
The Sexy Foxy!

171
00:11:41,620 --> 00:11:43,640
What exactly did you do
to change it like that?!

172
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:45,830
Cool! Cool!

173
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:47,050
Isn't it?

174
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:48,970
Listen to me!

175
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:52,420
So stupid!

176
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:55,190
It's been a long time since the last time
we saw that Jolly Roger.

177
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,230
That drawing stinks!

178
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:01,320
You drew it!

179
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:06,330
I've never forgotten about it
even for a day or a second!

180
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:11,330
I jumped into this New World
using the frustration from losing you as a springboard!

181
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:14,190
Scraped together some
very powerful crew members!

182
00:12:14,190 --> 00:12:16,360
Through Davy Back Fights?

183
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:21,880
That's right!
I just got an incredible guy the other day!

184
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:26,680
Let me introduce him!
He's a shipwright who rebuilt the ship beautifully!

185
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:31,490
A true artisan! "Gimmick" Dojaku!

186
00:12:33,170 --> 00:12:36,690
Hmmm, I kind of like your work.

187
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:39,690
What an honor to be praised by you, Franky.

188
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,900
Well, you know, I'm a genius so...

189
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:48,740
In addition, let me introduce our military tactician
who worked out the plan to bring you here!

190
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,750
He's a super strategist!

191
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:12,100
All you Straw Hats!
Nice to meet you!

192
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:16,660
I'm Komei from the Foxy Pirates!

193
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:25,150
People call me "White Feather" Komei!
I'm pleased to make your acquaintance!

194
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:28,100
He doesn't look like a military tactician.

195
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:32,230
But his humor definitely matches
Foxy's people.

196
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:37,460
Believe or not,
Komei used to be in the Navy!

197
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:39,960
The Navy?

198
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:44,310
How is that possible?!
Why did a Navy man become a pirate?!

199
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:46,990
Because I defeated him in a Davy Back Fight!

200
00:13:46,990 --> 00:13:49,040
Well, but still...

201
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,450
Rules are meant to be followed.

202
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:55,790
I was in the Navy but I've always been
a man of the sea at the same time.

203
00:13:56,330 --> 00:14:01,440
When you accept a challenge and lose,
you must join the other crew with good grace.

204
00:14:06,230 --> 00:14:09,160
Is that something to say proudly?
So stupid!

205
00:14:09,260 --> 00:14:12,990
We still have more and more incredible guys
so look forward to meeting them!

206
00:14:13,490 --> 00:14:18,290
Now, there's only one reason I lured you here!
You know what it is, don't you?

207
00:14:18,310 --> 00:14:23,250
A rematch of a Davy Back Fight!
Of course, you'll accept it, won't you?!

208
00:14:28,990 --> 00:14:33,310
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

209
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:36,790
It's getting interesting.

210
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:40,710
You've got to be kidding!
Luffy, don't accept it!

211
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:42,430
That's impossible.

212
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:46,550
A man can't turn his back
in a situation like this.

213
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:51,010
Boy!
Why are pirates such a bunch of idiots?!

214
00:15:03,690 --> 00:15:06,070
But it sounds like fun.

215
00:15:06,070 --> 00:15:11,680
Well, we know what kind of tricks they use
so I don't think we'll lose any this time.

216
00:15:16,830 --> 00:15:17,890
<i>TAKOYAKI</i>

217
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,600
Keep going! Keep going!

218
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:33,280
--Can I get 50 pieces of <i>okonomiyaki</i>?
--Okay!

219
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,780
Here! Here!
Would you like some frankfurters?

220
00:15:35,890 --> 00:15:38,660
L-O-V-E Boss!

221
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:43,380
--Would you like to have more? Free refill!
--Oh, thanks.

222
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,730
They're totally having a good time already.

223
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:48,940
The vibe is awesome! I love it!

224
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:51,990
By the way, what's that Davy thing?

225
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:57,130
You don't know?
It's an old game between two pirate crews.

226
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:01,810
The winner can pick out a crew member
from the loser's crew.

227
00:16:02,250 --> 00:16:07,820
Chopper was freaking out
because he was forced to join them once.

228
00:16:08,590 --> 00:16:11,840
--But you guys won it, didn't you?
--Yeah.

229
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:14,090
Did you take somebody from their crew?

230
00:16:14,090 --> 00:16:17,260
No, what we took was their Jolly Roger.
Their symbol.

231
00:16:17,260 --> 00:16:21,500
To make up for it, Luffy drew that but...

232
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,920
There!

233
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:25,690
FOX

234
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:25,790
This sucks...!

235
00:16:25,790 --> 00:16:27,420
I feel sorry for them.

236
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,480
Hm? What's wrong?

237
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:33,000
Davy Back is a pirate game, right?

238
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,370
Why would a Navy man accept such a thing?

239
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,490
You're right...

240
00:16:36,490 --> 00:16:37,660
I have a bad feeling.

241
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:41,340
Want some? These are the special-edition
souvenirs from the Davy Back!

242
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:43,370
Oh, nice! I want some!

243
00:16:43,370 --> 00:16:45,650
Hey! Don't buy crap like that!

244
00:16:45,910 --> 00:16:47,880
Cool! He's really a robot!

245
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,510
Robot? No, cyborg.

246
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:51,880
Cool! A robot language!

247
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,430
<i>Super!</i>

248
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,160
You, too! What are you doing?!

249
00:16:55,380 --> 00:16:59,850
Okay! As always, it's time for the pledge to follow
these three rules about losing!

250
00:16:59,850 --> 00:17:04,870
First, the only way to take back
anything you lose in a Davy Back Fight,

251
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:08,420
is through another Davy Back Fight.

252
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:13,400
Second, anyone taken by the winner
must swear loyalty to that ship's captain.

253
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:18,470
Third, if your Jolly Roger is taken,
you can't ever display it again!

254
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:22,530
If you break these rules, you'll be considered
dishonorable pirates

255
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:25,890
and sent to Davy Jones' Locker!

256
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,230
Do you swear to uphold these rules?

257
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,940
I swear.

258
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:30,420
I <i>shwear</i>.

259
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:38,040
Okay! Then, I hereby announce this Three-Coin Game
to be played by standard rules!

260
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:42,420
All right! It finally begins!

261
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:46,750
The Foxy Pirates' revenge match!
A Davy Back Fight!

262
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:50,860
Our boss lost his first battle after 920 straight victories
to this redoubtable man,

263
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:52,570
Straw Hat Luffy!

264
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:56,760
However, after that,
he has been winning battle after battle!

265
00:17:56,760 --> 00:18:01,850
I'm sure it's gonna be a good match again!
Now, the much-anticipated first round!

266
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:08,330
The eating contest!
The food is mushrooms harvested from this island!

267
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:12,610
Oh, couldn't be luckier! I get to eat!

268
00:18:12,610 --> 00:18:15,300
Never seen those... Is it okay?

269
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:18,220
I guess. I'm practically immune to poison.

270
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:20,530
Maybe they'll blow up when you eat them.

271
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:23,540
Don't eat them!
I can't find that mushroom anywhere!

272
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:25,620
Hey! Is it really safe?

273
00:18:25,870 --> 00:18:27,940
It is. Right?

274
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:32,980
It's a new type of mushroom which has been
discovered recently but it's not poisonous.

275
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:34,090
Don't worry.

276
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:37,800
Okay! Let me introduce
the members of both teams!

277
00:18:37,820 --> 00:18:40,320
First, the Straw Hat team!

278
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:45,550
The captain, Luffy! The cook, Sanji!
The musician, Brook!

279
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:46,460
So stupid.

280
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:48,920
If I win, Nami-san,

281
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,810
--let me see your panties...
--I won't, you idiot!

282
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,610
The contender -
the Foxy team's members are...

283
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:56,510
..."Four-Footed Dash Freak" Hamburg!

284
00:18:56,980 --> 00:18:58,180
Count on me!

285
00:18:58,180 --> 00:19:01,010
The genius shipwright, Dojaku!

286
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:06,330
And the only girl competing in this round,
our idol, Porche-<i>chan</i>!

287
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:08,750
Ooh! Thank you for your support!

288
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:14,920
Now, I'll explain the rules
but it's quite simple.

289
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:20,380
Three members on each team.
Which one can eat more mushrooms?

290
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:22,180
It's a three-minute match.

291
00:19:22,180 --> 00:19:25,220
Both teams have the same amount -
we measured properly.

292
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:27,450
Will you be okay, Big Sis?

293
00:19:27,450 --> 00:19:30,560
Oh, no!
I'm a big eater even though I don't look like it.

294
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:33,420
Hmmm, they're grilled beautifully.

295
00:19:33,420 --> 00:19:35,520
I can eat all of them even on my own!

296
00:19:37,130 --> 00:19:43,160
You can count on me, too.
My stomach is actually like a bottomless pit.

297
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:47,700
Having said that,
I don't really have a stomach now though!

298
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:50,280
You got me there!

299
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,200
Objection!

300
00:19:52,910 --> 00:19:53,810
Komei?

301
00:19:53,810 --> 00:19:57,170
The Straw Hat team's
selection of members isn't fair.

302
00:19:57,190 --> 00:20:00,450
Huh? What? You have an objection
about the decision, you ex-Navy?

303
00:20:00,450 --> 00:20:01,430
That's right!

304
00:20:01,780 --> 00:20:06,200
Since it's an eating contest,
the competitors must have a stomach!

305
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:10,830
Brook the musician,
I think I must blow my whistle on you!

306
00:20:10,830 --> 00:20:12,480
Oh, you're right!

307
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,670
Oh, you're right!

308
00:20:15,670 --> 00:20:19,490
No, do you agree to it?!
They have to do it just the two of them, then!

309
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:21,300
I can do it on my own!

310
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:25,720
Idiot! Anything could happen!
Do you forget what happened the last time?!

311
00:20:25,940 --> 00:20:28,240
We almost lost Chopper to them!

312
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:34,400
Hey! It hasn't started yet! We'll accept his complaint
so allow us to change a member!

313
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:38,840
Don't be ridiculous!
"No change allowed in competitors" is in the rules, fool!

314
00:20:41,450 --> 00:20:45,260
Well, it's okay. Let's allow it.

315
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:49,870
They'll accept the complaint
so let's make an exception.

316
00:20:50,470 --> 00:20:52,100
Who will fill his shoes?!

317
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:57,340
Why is that newcomer going
over our boss' head?!

318
00:20:58,460 --> 00:20:59,800
Usopp.

319
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,770
I don't know what the other games will be like

320
00:21:02,770 --> 00:21:06,050
but the only one among us who eats as much as Luffy is him!

321
00:21:06,050 --> 00:21:07,990
Zoro! Can you do it?!

322
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,870
I have no choice. Damn!

323
00:21:11,230 --> 00:21:13,460
Let's just do it already!

324
00:21:19,270 --> 00:21:20,900
I'm sorry.

325
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:25,450
No problem at all.
I was just getting tired of drinking.

326
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:31,620
Usopp subbed in a useless lump!
We don't need the moss ball pickled in <i>sake</i>.

327
00:21:31,620 --> 00:21:36,130
I bet he became anxious because our pervert cook
keeps having nosebleeds.

328
00:21:37,790 --> 00:21:39,860
Cut it out, you two!

329
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:45,190
Okay! We have all members from both teams again!
It'll finally start!

330
00:21:45,190 --> 00:21:46,670
Oh, what is it?

331
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:52,680
Oops. Seems like we forgot to mention
one more rule.

332
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:57,590
It says "No one except for the competitors is
allowed to climb up on the stage."

333
00:21:57,590 --> 00:22:02,170
"If someone does it,
that team forfeits at that moment!"

334
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:03,860
Was there such a rule?

335
00:22:03,860 --> 00:22:05,550
Whatever! Just start already!

336
00:22:05,650 --> 00:22:08,910
All right! The first round starts now!

337
00:22:09,950 --> 00:22:15,410
It began! The fateful revenge match!
Who will win this thing?!

338
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:19,480
Oh, by the way,
I, Itomimizu, am your host...

339
00:22:20,090 --> 00:22:23,300
Oh, the Straw Hat team is in top gear already!

340
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,300
Seems like they're swallowing down
the mushrooms!

341
00:22:26,590 --> 00:22:28,460
Can't believe how they eat!

342
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:31,720
Now, the opponent, the Foxy team is...

343
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:33,680
Oh? Huh?!

344
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:37,350
Dojaku isn't doing anything!
What is he doing?!

345
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:39,150
Hey, why aren't you eating?!

346
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:41,250
I have a plan.

347
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:44,960
I'll make it up all at once later. Just wait.

348
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,450
Hamburg?!

349
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:54,890
Whoa...
What's wrong with you suddenly?! Hey!

350
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:58,470
Wh-What is going on?

351
00:23:00,330 --> 00:23:03,980
The Straw Hat team, too!
All of them stopped eating!

352
00:23:04,090 --> 00:23:06,420
Luffy! Zoro! Sanji!

353
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:07,700
Is it poison?!

354
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:12,870
Hamburg! Stay with me!
What happened to you?

355
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:15,790
Hey... Say something...

356
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:21,250
I can't believe it!
Everybody who was eating the mushrooms collapsed!

357
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,690
Chopper! Meds!

358
00:23:22,690 --> 00:23:26,760
No! If I can't figure out what kind of poison it is,
I can't neutralize it!

359
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:29,050
Damn! Let's go closer to them!

360
00:23:29,150 --> 00:23:30,070
Uh-huh!

361
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,760
No, wait!

362
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,680
What?!

363
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:36,410
If you climb up on the stage, you people lose.

364
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:40,440
--Hey! This is not time to argue about it!
--It's an emergency!

365
00:23:40,540 --> 00:23:42,400
The rule is the rule.

366
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,480
Is he nuts?!

367
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:48,840
Boss! Let's call off the Davy Back Fight!

368
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,090
Y-Yeah...

369
00:23:50,090 --> 00:23:53,410
Oh? Do you want to call off the fight
that's already been started?

370
00:23:53,410 --> 00:23:56,060
Shut up! Your crewmates are suffering!

371
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:59,980
In the first place, you came up with the eating contest!

372
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:02,520
How will you take the responsibility for it?!

373
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:06,050
I told you they're not poisonous.
They won't die.

374
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:10,320
Then, how do you explain what's going on
on that stage?!

375
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:14,180
Well, just watch what happens. Dojaku!

376
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:16,240
--Okay!
--What?

377
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,470
D-Dojaku?

378
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:30,440
Oh! The two from the Foxy team are
getting up!

379
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:34,780
All of the Straw Hat team are
already sitting up, too!

380
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:37,370
--Luffy!
--Are they alright?

381
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:41,750
Luffy! Zoro! Sanji! Are you conscious?!
Feeling numb somewhere in your body?!

382
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,650
Feeling nauseous?!

383
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:45,440
I feel sick...

384
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:48,370
Feeling sick?! What else?!

385
00:24:48,370 --> 00:24:51,520
At least, you're up so this will do!

386
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:54,110
What are you trying to make someone
who got food poisoning eat?!

387
00:24:54,110 --> 00:24:56,370
Eat this and perk up!

388
00:25:02,790 --> 00:25:03,940
Don't wanna it.

389
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:06,520
--Luffy?!
--What did he just say?

390
00:25:07,210 --> 00:25:13,610
Oh? What? Straw Hat doesn't look good.
It's not just my imagination, is it?

391
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:17,300
--I don't wanna move.
--I'll stay still.

392
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:19,080
Huh?! So are they?!

393
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,260
Oh, no...

394
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:25,040
So are our executives!
What's going on?!

395
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,610
--What happened?!
--It doesn't look like them.

396
00:25:27,610 --> 00:25:30,980
Don't tell me it's because of that mushroom?

397
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,670
That's right!

398
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,820
Komei, you...

399
00:25:35,820 --> 00:25:37,410
Oh? He's gone.

400
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:38,900
I'm up here.

401
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:43,770
--When did you get there?!
--Soldiers value speed above quality.

402
00:25:43,770 --> 00:25:47,400
How was it?
What an amazing tactic! It's called...

403
00:25:47,420 --> 00:25:50,380
A-SINGLE-BITE IMMOBILIZATION MANEUVER

404
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:50,380
"A-Single-Bite Immobilization Maneuver"!

405
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:54,110
What?! Why did you do as you like,
without my permission!

406
00:25:54,260 --> 00:25:56,900
Because I didn't need your permission.

407
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:58,200
Dojaku!

408
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:00,100
Okay!

409
00:26:00,260 --> 00:26:02,490
What, what? Whaaat?!

410
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,940
--What's that?!
--Is it a cage?!

411
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:16,080
--Did he cage them along with their own crewmates?!
--Luffy!

412
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:18,820
What?! Was there such a rule?!

413
00:26:20,330 --> 00:26:23,110
You fool, what are you doing?!

414
00:26:23,110 --> 00:26:25,610
What will you do to my subordinates as well as the others?!

415
00:26:25,610 --> 00:26:28,000
I have no interest in those two!
They were just in the way!

416
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,630
What?

417
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:32,360
My target is the Straw Hats!

418
00:26:32,670 --> 00:26:37,570
My biggest goal is to capture all of them!

419
00:26:39,850 --> 00:26:41,220
Luffy!

420
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:44,410
That jerk!
I thought there was something behind this!

421
00:26:44,410 --> 00:26:50,270
Enough already! You lost the Davy Back
and became my subordinate so...

422
00:26:50,270 --> 00:26:52,290
...you can't do as you like!

423
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,630
Be quiet!

424
00:26:54,530 --> 00:26:58,950
There's no way I become
a subordinate of someone like you!

425
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:04,000
I lost to you so I could
accomplish my own plan!

426
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:09,090
In order to put the Straw Hats off their guard,
I wanted to draw them into the game!

427
00:27:09,090 --> 00:27:09,960
What, what...

428
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:15,170
It was for my tactic but still it was so humiliating
to work under you!

429
00:27:15,170 --> 00:27:16,740
--Your tactic?
--Yes!

430
00:27:16,800 --> 00:27:20,550
STRAW HAT ERADICATION MANEUVER

431
00:27:17,830 --> 00:27:19,960
"Straw Hat Eradication Maneuver"!

432
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,740
Split-Head! What is it all about?!

433
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:25,540
I-I don't quite know, either...

434
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:27,910
I'm done talking to you!

435
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:38,010
Oh, no!
He's gonna take them along with the cage!

436
00:27:38,110 --> 00:27:39,630
Good job.

437
00:27:41,990 --> 00:27:47,560
Whoa-whoa!
Where are you taking our captain and the others?

438
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,480
So solid!

439
00:27:52,580 --> 00:27:55,320
You bastard! What have you done?!

440
00:27:55,690 --> 00:27:58,340
I already told you. Weren't you listening...

441
00:27:58,340 --> 00:28:00,860
I'm asking you what you made them eat!

442
00:28:02,190 --> 00:28:05,560
It was the Drowsy Mushroom that grows naturally only on this island.

443
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:10,270
Those who eat it will lose
all of their fighting spirit, they say.

444
00:28:10,270 --> 00:28:14,380
That's why you quibbled about me.
To make us switch!

445
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:15,540
That's right!

446
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:19,340
I knew Pirate Hunter would be called in
to fill your shoes!

447
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:22,150
--Chopper! It's a Drowsy Mushroom!
--Okay!

448
00:28:22,150 --> 00:28:25,260
--How is it?! Is it there?!
--It's no use!

449
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:29,730
It was discovered recently.
There's no way it's in the book!

450
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:34,790
So far, there is only one way to free someone
from the effects of a Drowsy Mushroom.

451
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:39,740
Eat a Rebound Mushroom
which also grows naturally on this island.

452
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,780
I see. So that's it.

453
00:28:42,010 --> 00:28:43,090
What?

454
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,360
I'm back!

455
00:28:51,560 --> 00:28:53,580
--Yeah!
--Well done, Robin!

456
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:55,930
Oh, damn you! Straw Hat is...

457
00:28:55,930 --> 00:28:56,920
That's okay.

458
00:28:57,900 --> 00:28:59,920
Let's pull the cage in.

459
00:29:00,030 --> 00:29:01,470
Roger!

460
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:13,100
Oh, no! Luffy!

461
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:14,120
Okay!

462
00:29:17,710 --> 00:29:20,240
What a fool! I can't even bend them...

463
00:29:23,340 --> 00:29:24,680
Is it for real?!

464
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,660
Hey, Zoro! Sanji! Let's get out!

465
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:28,910
--Hey!
--Luffy, behind you!

466
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:39,420
Zoro! Sanji!

467
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:51,430
Now, my subordinates!
Show yourselves!

468
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:57,440
Ship-bottom squad here!
We're all ready!

469
00:29:57,760 --> 00:30:00,900
Great. We'll withdraw!

470
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:11,350
No! The ship is leaving!

471
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:13,500
Bastard! You can't go anywhere!

472
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:19,130
Dammit!

473
00:30:19,410 --> 00:30:21,550
Gum-Gum Rocket...

474
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:24,670
--Luffy!
--He's standing on the sand so...

475
00:30:25,030 --> 00:30:30,090
Damn! Give back my friends!

476
00:30:30,090 --> 00:30:33,130
Right. I knew that's what you'd do.

477
00:30:43,130 --> 00:30:45,240
--Luffy!
--Oh, no! He fell into the sea!

478
00:30:45,600 --> 00:30:48,720
It deflects pursuers with a slick coating.
It's called...

479
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:53,270
SLIPPING OIL SLICK MANEUVER

480
00:30:49,020 --> 00:30:51,010
"Slipping Oil Slick Maneuver"!

481
00:30:51,010 --> 00:30:53,270
You just put the oil there...

482
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:58,620
<i>Dammit...</i>

483
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:01,000
Komei!

484
00:31:01,610 --> 00:31:05,300
Even if you can roar,
there's nothing you can do.

485
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:09,090
Straw Hats!

486
00:31:09,490 --> 00:31:13,720
I'm sure it's frustrating and
you want to save your friends.

487
00:31:14,190 --> 00:31:17,790
I won't run or hide! Come see me!

488
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:18,840
Here!

489
00:31:20,830 --> 00:31:22,650
An Eternal Pose?

490
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,370
I'll be expecting you!

491
00:31:26,340 --> 00:31:30,570
Don't underestimate me!
I have an ace in the hole!

492
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,700
Slow-Slow Beam!

493
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,870
That beam, huh?!

494
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:41,830
What the...!

495
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:51,200
I knew you'd do that.
And I had a countermeasure.

496
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:55,330
We thought this would happen
so I created something.

497
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:57,560
It's an interception for the Slow-Slow beam!

498
00:31:57,580 --> 00:32:00,040
"Specular Reflection Maneuver"!

499
00:31:57,580 --> 00:32:00,750
SPECULAR REFLECTION MANEUVER

500
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:03,610
Daaammmnnn...

501
00:32:07,170 --> 00:32:11,050
Now, struggle with my maneuvers!

502
00:32:11,050 --> 00:32:16,850
Straw Hat Luffy!
Your friends' lives are in my hands!

503
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:24,700
Pirate Hunter and Black-Foot
can't even move now.

504
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:28,240
But the key one, Straw Hat is...

505
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,990
I saw it coming.

506
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:34,610
I knew they'd rip off the Rebound Mushroom
and cure Straw Hat first, as well.

507
00:32:34,610 --> 00:32:36,580
Oh, you did?

508
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:41,750
We'll move on to the second plan from now.
Tell everyone!

509
00:32:41,750 --> 00:32:42,730
Yes, sir!

510
00:32:58,520 --> 00:33:00,390
We're back!

511
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:09,400
What's that Slow-Slow crap?

512
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:11,630
Foxy's a Devil Fruit eater, too.

513
00:33:12,110 --> 00:33:14,760
He ate the Slow-Slow Fruit
and became a slow human.

514
00:33:14,780 --> 00:33:18,640
When someone or something is
exposed to his Slow-Slow Beam,

515
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:22,500
it will become slow for 30 seconds.

516
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:26,130
It was longer than I expected. 30 seconds.

517
00:33:26,130 --> 00:33:30,280
But the eater himself became slow-slow, too.
How hopeless he is.

518
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,820
Zoro... Sanji...

519
00:33:35,210 --> 00:33:39,870
If they wanted to capture us, they could
but why did they leave?

520
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:44,330
The fact he told us about the Rebound Mushroom
is illogical, too.

521
00:33:45,350 --> 00:33:47,090
You're right.

522
00:33:47,730 --> 00:33:51,090
In addition, he invited us with this.

523
00:33:51,090 --> 00:33:53,170
It's a trap, isn't it?

524
00:33:53,170 --> 00:33:54,540
Probably.

525
00:33:55,490 --> 00:33:59,260
That vice admiral seemed like quite a tactician.

526
00:34:07,580 --> 00:34:08,840
Let's go!

527
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:12,190
That's right!
Even if it's a trap, we gotta do it!

528
00:34:12,670 --> 00:34:15,700
Let's save Zoro-<i>san</i> and Sanji-<i>san</i>!

529
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:18,280
We must bring them to their senses!

530
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:20,780
We gotta find the Rebound Mushroom first!

531
00:34:20,780 --> 00:34:22,810
I'll look for it!

532
00:34:22,810 --> 00:34:25,130
Is this enough of a lead for you?

533
00:34:27,190 --> 00:34:30,020
Do you still smell the Rebound Mushroom?

534
00:34:30,020 --> 00:34:32,860
Uh-huh! I'll look for it following the scent!

535
00:34:33,940 --> 00:34:36,470
I'll come with you.

536
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:43,060
If I separate my body and soul,
there is no limit to my field of search!

537
00:34:44,330 --> 00:34:47,830
Straw Hat, you got an awesome guy
as your crew member!

538
00:34:47,830 --> 00:34:49,730
Brook is living a super long life!

539
00:34:49,730 --> 00:34:52,230
I don't think you call it a long life...

540
00:34:55,010 --> 00:34:56,340
I'm sorry.

541
00:34:57,470 --> 00:35:00,430
I'm the only one who got to eat
the Rebound Mushroom.

542
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:02,590
Right back at you.

543
00:35:03,050 --> 00:35:07,580
Because I kind of set you guys up...
I'm sorry.

544
00:35:12,190 --> 00:35:16,240
Luffy! You go ahead!
I'll catch up with you after I find it.

545
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:17,510
Got it!

546
00:35:17,610 --> 00:35:19,660
Chopper, use it.

547
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:20,850
Thank you.

548
00:35:22,030 --> 00:35:25,120
--Then, take these.
--Yeah.

549
00:35:25,780 --> 00:35:28,040
I'll hand them over to him at any cost!

550
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:29,900
Both of you! I'm counting on you!

551
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,340
--Okay!
--Yes!

552
00:35:34,590 --> 00:35:36,360
Straw Hat!

553
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:47,750
You're not the only one
who got your crew members taken!

554
00:35:50,150 --> 00:35:52,060
They took our ship, too!

555
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:55,800
I know I have no right to ask
something like this.

556
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:59,090
But I wanna save my friends, too!

557
00:36:00,570 --> 00:36:02,340
Boss...

558
00:36:03,450 --> 00:36:05,310
Let me get on board.

559
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,000
Please!

560
00:36:10,750 --> 00:36:12,850
Boss...!

561
00:36:21,180 --> 00:36:22,220
Come on board!

562
00:36:24,180 --> 00:36:25,280
Split-Head!

563
00:36:28,230 --> 00:36:30,710
You called me Split-Head again...

564
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,290
Boss!

565
00:36:34,610 --> 00:36:37,110
Say something back! Say something back!

566
00:36:37,110 --> 00:36:39,050
Don't let it bother you!

567
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:44,660
It's no time for feeling down, guys!

568
00:36:44,660 --> 00:36:45,600
Yeah!

569
00:36:46,240 --> 00:36:48,770
I'm in debt to you, Straw Hat!

570
00:36:48,870 --> 00:36:51,350
Cut the crap and get on board already!

571
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,110
Boss!

572
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:56,770
Okay! Everyone, get on board!

573
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:58,900
Yeah!

574
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:01,050
No, we can't have all of them!

575
00:37:01,050 --> 00:37:03,510
It's obvious that it'll be overloaded!

576
00:37:03,510 --> 00:37:05,870
Think about the size of the ship!

577
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:08,220
Wait! Wait! Wait!

578
00:37:08,850 --> 00:37:12,880
I appreciate your commitment!
But I'm responsible for this!

579
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,880
Will you leave it in my hands?

580
00:37:16,190 --> 00:37:20,840
I will rescue Porche and Hamburg
no matter what!

581
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,880
Excuse me, Boss!

582
00:37:28,490 --> 00:37:30,250
Kansho, what is it?

583
00:37:30,250 --> 00:37:33,060
I really want you to take me with you!

584
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:37,860
I've just joined your crew
so I wanna do something for you!

585
00:37:39,510 --> 00:37:40,820
Also...

586
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,400
<i>Senpai</i>!

587
00:37:43,930 --> 00:37:45,780
Me? <i>Senpai</i>?

588
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:49,370
Your sniping skill was as amazing as they say.
I'm impressed!

589
00:37:49,390 --> 00:37:51,850
That's really consummate skill!

590
00:37:51,850 --> 00:37:54,000
Well, that's too much to say...!

591
00:37:54,230 --> 00:37:58,040
The Navy is our enemy!
I know he'll use projectile weapons, too!

592
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:00,170
Gun for gun!

593
00:38:00,190 --> 00:38:02,630
I'm sure I can help you!

594
00:38:02,650 --> 00:38:05,090
Okay, you get on board, too!
<i>Kancho</i> (goosie) !

595
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:08,970
My name is KanSHO!

596
00:38:09,330 --> 00:38:10,540
Okay!

597
00:38:10,860 --> 00:38:12,810
Refueling completed!

598
00:38:12,810 --> 00:38:14,770
We're ready, Luffy!

599
00:38:16,210 --> 00:38:17,690
All right!

600
00:38:17,690 --> 00:38:21,070
Sunny! Sail out!

601
00:38:37,650 --> 00:38:39,400
We gotta go, too!

602
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,210
Yes, let's go!

603
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,530
Hey, you two!

604
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,740
We'll help you!

605
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:48,390
It's better to have more people
for the search!

606
00:38:51,740 --> 00:38:53,100
Thank you!

607
00:38:57,170 --> 00:39:01,360
The Davy Back Fight...
I wish I could play some new games...

608
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:04,590
I can't believe I'll fight together with you.

609
00:39:04,590 --> 00:39:08,160
We have the same purpose so it's good.

610
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:18,010
Since I lost to you it has been terrible.

611
00:39:31,410 --> 00:39:35,790
FOX

612
00:39:31,700 --> 00:39:35,790
<i>That Jolly Roger became a symbol of losing.</i>

613
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,250
<i>No matter how many Davy Back Fights I won,</i>

614
00:39:40,250 --> 00:39:42,750
<i>as long as we have that Jolly Roger,</i>

615
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:47,550
<i>the label "the man who got defeated by Straw Hat"
has stuck with me.</i>

616
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:52,570
<i>But Komei didn't laugh at me.</i>

617
00:39:54,220 --> 00:39:56,750
As long as you're tied to your past,

618
00:39:57,180 --> 00:39:59,960
it's the same as time standing still.

619
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:13,330
That was also a part of his plan, though.

620
00:40:14,870 --> 00:40:17,370
Well, this doesn't sound like me, does it?!

621
00:40:17,370 --> 00:40:18,740
Nope! It doesn't!

622
00:40:21,290 --> 00:40:24,460
You always say things straight out,
every single time!

623
00:40:24,460 --> 00:40:26,840
Because it really doesn't sound like you!

624
00:40:29,300 --> 00:40:30,950
You didn't need to tell me again...

625
00:40:31,300 --> 00:40:33,910
Zoro was my first crew member.

626
00:40:34,260 --> 00:40:38,040
My first crew members were
Porche and Hamburg.

627
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:42,280
No matter how many crew members have come and gone through Davy Back Fights,

628
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:44,510
they've always been with me.

629
00:40:54,740 --> 00:40:59,060
When I become the King of the Pirates,
none of them can be left behind.

630
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:01,650
It shouldn't be without them.

631
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,600
They're my friends!

632
00:41:12,930 --> 00:41:16,740
As a token of our friendship, I'll give you this!

633
00:41:18,310 --> 00:41:19,930
Thank you!

634
00:41:19,930 --> 00:41:21,870
While I'm at it, here's a big treat!

635
00:41:22,250 --> 00:41:24,860
All of you Straw Hats can have it!

636
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:28,920
Don't want it.

637
00:41:30,190 --> 00:41:32,420
Why don't you guys put it on, too?

638
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:36,010
It's embarrassing as a human being!

639
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,470
I'll pass on it...

640
00:41:37,580 --> 00:41:40,100
What?! But it's cool...

641
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:44,770
It's so hot!

642
00:41:44,770 --> 00:41:48,270
The two opposing groups join hands
and challenge the formidable enemy!

643
00:41:48,660 --> 00:41:49,840
<i>Senpai</i>, have one!

644
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,570
No, I really don't want it.

645
00:41:51,670 --> 00:41:53,780
Eat it! In return for the pin-badge!

646
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:55,390
Straw Hat!

647
00:41:55,390 --> 00:41:58,740
--Let's energize ourselves and create havoc!
--Yeah!

648
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:07,000
Wait for me! Fan guy!

649
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,700
Should we leave them like this?

650
00:42:17,700 --> 00:42:23,740
I have no interest in the Foxy Pirates
but since they're pirates, we can't let them free.

651
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:26,810
We'll execute them along with the Straw Hats!

652
00:42:33,090 --> 00:42:35,770
All serene. They're still quiet.

653
00:42:39,260 --> 00:42:43,450
They're ill-famed tough guys but
how pathetic.

654
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:47,430
I'll throw the rest of your crew in here soon!

655
00:42:48,020 --> 00:42:49,710
Wait for it!

656
00:42:54,740 --> 00:42:55,920
This isn't it...

657
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:57,300
Not it, either!

658
00:42:57,700 --> 00:42:59,010
How about this?

659
00:43:01,330 --> 00:43:03,370
This isn't it, either!

660
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:07,110
Well, we have to
just keep looking for it patiently!

661
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:19,680
Boy! I thought my heart was gonna explode!

662
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:22,430
Although I don't have a heart.

663
00:43:30,770 --> 00:43:35,460
--It's because of this mushroom.
--Let's call it a Sneeze Mushroom.

664
00:43:35,490 --> 00:43:38,860
Hey! What the...
Did something happen to you?

665
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:41,280
No! Stay away!

666
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:46,560
--I said...
--"Stay away."

667
00:43:47,750 --> 00:43:49,770
What a huge steel trap!

668
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:53,020
Don't tell me you guys set it up.

669
00:43:53,350 --> 00:43:55,430
No way! Look!

670
00:43:56,170 --> 00:43:57,660
At this!

671
00:43:56,170 --> 00:43:58,840
APPROVED BY KOMEI

672
00:43:58,860 --> 00:44:02,440
What an easy-to-understand person
Komei is...

673
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:05,330
Brook?

674
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,080
Shh! The atmosphere changed.

675
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:12,270
I can sense it with my bones literally.

676
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:14,750
We're under siege.

677
00:44:16,610 --> 00:44:18,070
Duck!

678
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:33,500
Is that the island?

679
00:44:33,500 --> 00:44:35,940
No mistake!
The needle is pointing towards it!

680
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:42,530
I see a pirate ship in the west.

681
00:44:42,550 --> 00:44:44,850
<i>It's the Straw Hats' Jolly Roger!</i>

682
00:44:44,850 --> 00:44:46,240
Here they come.

683
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:48,040
Be ready to ambush!

684
00:44:48,040 --> 00:44:50,890
Arrange in the crane-wing formation
and surround them!

685
00:44:50,890 --> 00:44:51,980
<i>Yes, sir!</i>

686
00:44:55,570 --> 00:44:57,550
They were lying in wait as I thought!

687
00:44:57,550 --> 00:45:00,990
They'll attack us from both sides.
This is not good.

688
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:04,450
If they're not in front of us,
we can't even use the Gaon Cannon!

689
00:45:04,450 --> 00:45:09,850
I did research.
I also know that they don't have enough gunners.

690
00:45:11,870 --> 00:45:13,670
Oh, no! They started shooting already!

691
00:45:13,670 --> 00:45:15,090
What about the Coup de Burst?

692
00:45:15,090 --> 00:45:17,570
No! It's too late!

693
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:21,450
Leave it to me!

694
00:45:21,580 --> 00:45:23,360
Slow-Slow...

695
00:45:23,390 --> 00:45:25,220
...Beam!

696
00:45:29,600 --> 00:45:31,000
And...

697
00:45:31,060 --> 00:45:32,830
Slower! Slower!

698
00:45:32,830 --> 00:45:33,920
Slower!

699
00:45:33,940 --> 00:45:35,520
Slower! Slower! Slower!

700
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,060
Slower! Slower! Slower!

701
00:45:42,070 --> 00:45:43,950
Wow! They stopped!

702
00:45:43,950 --> 00:45:45,950
What?! It's awesome!

703
00:45:45,950 --> 00:45:50,930
It's not completely stopped
but when I use Slower-Slower, this is what happens.

704
00:45:50,950 --> 00:45:52,210
Cool!

705
00:45:52,210 --> 00:45:55,350
--How long will it last?
--30 seconds, of course.

706
00:45:55,350 --> 00:45:56,940
30 seconds, again?!

707
00:45:56,960 --> 00:45:58,130
That's not so great.

708
00:45:58,130 --> 00:46:02,300
Shut up! You don't know how tough it was
to master it!

709
00:46:02,300 --> 00:46:06,430
There was a tearjerking story!
You wanna hear it?

710
00:46:06,430 --> 00:46:07,950
--Not at all.
--Too quick!

711
00:46:08,060 --> 00:46:09,830
Almost 30 seconds already.

712
00:46:09,830 --> 00:46:12,160
Oh yeah! Franky!

713
00:46:12,310 --> 00:46:17,440
It's ready thanks to that!
Hold on really tight!

714
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:20,230
Coup de Burst!

715
00:46:35,580 --> 00:46:38,400
Oh! The Navy ships are...

716
00:46:38,420 --> 00:46:42,210
--Boss, you did it!
--Six ships got wrecked!

717
00:46:42,210 --> 00:46:46,180
See that?!
That's the power of the Slower-Slower!

718
00:46:46,180 --> 00:46:48,160
I like it! Slower-Slower!

719
00:46:48,550 --> 00:46:50,510
It's useful depending on how you use it.

720
00:46:50,510 --> 00:46:53,210
Well, it's a pain if the user is our enemy.

721
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:59,250
<i>A-All ships have been wrecked!
The Straw Hats broke through the ambush fleet!</i>

722
00:46:59,270 --> 00:47:02,950
<i></i><i>Confirming seven from the pirate ship landed on the island!</i>

723
00:47:02,950 --> 00:47:05,090
<i>They're climbing the outer rim of the crater!</i>

724
00:47:05,450 --> 00:47:10,510
I got a report that two Devil Fruit eaters
have remained on the Mushroom Island.

725
00:47:11,910 --> 00:47:13,370
That's good.

726
00:47:13,790 --> 00:47:17,310
That's the point of giving them information
about the Rebound Mushroom.

727
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:24,510
Hey, Split-Head, you're behind.

728
00:47:24,510 --> 00:47:25,880
Shut up!

729
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:27,760
Boss, you can do it!

730
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:31,870
I can go Slow-Slow but I don't like to hustle!

731
00:47:34,020 --> 00:47:35,960
What's with this island?

732
00:47:44,650 --> 00:47:47,820
What do you call it? A caldera?

733
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:51,510
There is something that looks like a volcanic vent in the basin.

734
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:56,460
But that looks like water vapor
instead of volcanic smoke.

735
00:47:57,830 --> 00:48:01,150
But it's definitely a Navy base.

736
00:48:01,510 --> 00:48:04,790
I see building-like things everywhere
on the rock towers.

737
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:09,360
They seem to say,
"We're not gonna let you get away no matter what!"

738
00:48:09,380 --> 00:48:11,740
There are more warships.

739
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:16,600
I see some human figures on the outer rim.

740
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:21,560
One, two... There are seven.
I assume they're the Straw Hats.

741
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:23,420
Report to the vice admiral!

742
00:48:23,650 --> 00:48:26,760
Okay. Put the second plan in motion.

743
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:30,260
<i>Welcome, people of the Straw Hats!</i>

744
00:48:30,820 --> 00:48:32,170
<i></i><i>I'm a special operation adviser</i>

745
00:48:32,170 --> 00:48:37,290
<i>from the Strategies/Tactics
Research and Development Division of the Navy -</i>

746
00:48:37,290 --> 00:48:39,670
<i></i><i>Vice Admiral Komei!</i>

747
00:48:39,670 --> 00:48:40,810
Too long...

748
00:48:40,920 --> 00:48:42,920
Where are you, Fan guy?!

749
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:47,230
<i>Do you think I'll tell you guys that honestly?</i>

750
00:48:47,550 --> 00:48:51,800
<i>Well, I'll just say somewhere on
one of those rock towers.</i>

751
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:54,180
<i>Your friends are there, too.</i>

752
00:48:54,180 --> 00:48:58,230
He's using echoes quite effectively.
I can't tell where he's speaking from.

753
00:48:58,230 --> 00:49:02,290
One of those rock towers?
There are tons of those!

754
00:49:02,400 --> 00:49:03,980
Do you think it's true?

755
00:49:04,110 --> 00:49:08,320
It's fifty-fifty.
I can't deny the chance that he's telling the truth.

756
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:12,870
Don't make it so frustrating!
I thought your target was me!

757
00:49:12,870 --> 00:49:15,390
<i>It's all of you.</i>

758
00:49:15,780 --> 00:49:18,500
I suggest you to try your best and find them.

759
00:49:18,500 --> 00:49:23,830
Hmmm, let me think.
I'll give you plenty of time.

760
00:49:23,830 --> 00:49:26,840
How about until the break of day tomorrow?

761
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:32,200
If you can rescue them before
the sun rises above the horizon, you win.

762
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:38,770
If you fail, you guys will
fall into my clutches on this island.

763
00:49:43,690 --> 00:49:46,230
All of us are his target, he said.

764
00:49:46,230 --> 00:49:50,590
It was an apparent provocation.
There are obviously some traps.

765
00:49:50,590 --> 00:49:52,450
I guess.

766
00:49:52,450 --> 00:49:54,910
Oh, my chronic disease of... um...

767
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:56,330
Enough with that!

768
00:49:56,330 --> 00:49:57,450
Okay.

769
00:49:57,910 --> 00:49:59,830
But we're going, aren't we?

770
00:49:59,830 --> 00:50:01,520
Yes, we are!

771
00:50:01,910 --> 00:50:03,120
I thought so.

772
00:50:03,120 --> 00:50:06,320
It can't be helped that
the Navy will come after us.

773
00:50:06,790 --> 00:50:10,170
But whatever your target is,

774
00:50:12,380 --> 00:50:16,160
I'll find and save my friends at any cost!

775
00:50:18,640 --> 00:50:20,240
Great.

776
00:50:20,270 --> 00:50:22,590
He's so cool!

777
00:50:22,590 --> 00:50:24,790
That's what I expect from the man that I think highly of.

778
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:29,380
"Try to find them"?
I don't wanna take it slow like that!

779
00:50:30,650 --> 00:50:33,010
I'll destroy them all at once!

780
00:50:33,110 --> 00:50:35,910
What?! But your friends are in one of the towers!

781
00:50:35,910 --> 00:50:40,370
We can't stop him now.
Well, I'm sure they'll be fine.

782
00:50:40,370 --> 00:50:42,020
Is it like that?

783
00:50:42,120 --> 00:50:45,120
Ho-hum. We have no choice but to go along as I thought.

784
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:46,040
Yeah.

785
00:50:47,080 --> 00:50:51,190
Gum-Gum...

786
00:50:54,050 --> 00:50:58,410
...Hawk Gatling!

787
00:51:14,740 --> 00:51:17,070
--What? What's the matter?
--My strength...

788
00:51:17,070 --> 00:51:19,140
What?! What?!
What did they do to you?!

789
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:21,010
<i>It feels like...</i>

790
00:51:25,620 --> 00:51:28,330
--Hey!
--You, too?! What happened?!

791
00:51:28,330 --> 00:51:32,960
I don't know!
I felt something grabbed me and...

792
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:36,040
...now I'm losing my strength!

793
00:51:36,040 --> 00:51:38,570
--Is it Sea Prism Stone?
--A bit different!

794
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:42,470
It's coiling around my hands...

795
00:51:42,470 --> 00:51:45,950
Or like some plant creeping around
my hands...

796
00:51:46,060 --> 00:51:48,350
--What's that?!
--Oh my!

797
00:51:48,350 --> 00:51:50,870
Are you getting pulled
by your own stretching force?!

798
00:51:51,770 --> 00:51:54,670
Really?! What is that plant?!

799
00:51:55,030 --> 00:51:56,860
What do you think has happened?!

800
00:51:56,860 --> 00:52:00,340
I don't know. Straw Hat and the other one lost it all of a sudden.

801
00:52:02,660 --> 00:52:03,760
Watch out!

802
00:52:11,170 --> 00:52:12,730
Star Shield!

803
00:52:12,730 --> 00:52:13,710
That?!

804
00:52:27,520 --> 00:52:28,940
Perfect!

805
00:52:28,940 --> 00:52:30,520
Far from it!

806
00:52:31,810 --> 00:52:34,000
Oh? Where's Robin?

807
00:52:34,440 --> 00:52:36,070
That plant again...

808
00:52:43,990 --> 00:52:47,690
Robin?! Hey, Robin?!
Where are you?! Answer me!

809
00:52:50,330 --> 00:52:51,690
Are you there?

810
00:52:51,790 --> 00:52:55,670
What the hell is wrong with this plant?
It's coiling around my hands!

811
00:52:55,670 --> 00:52:56,980
Boss!

812
00:52:57,760 --> 00:52:59,880
Where's Robin?!

813
00:52:59,880 --> 00:53:03,200
--I don't know! I really don't know!
--Boss!

814
00:53:04,390 --> 00:53:09,210
What is this plant?!
It doesn't look like it's moving or anything...

815
00:53:10,440 --> 00:53:14,060
Strong smell of the sea!
Don't tell me it's...

816
00:53:14,060 --> 00:53:16,030
<i>You have quite quick wits.</i>

817
00:53:17,230 --> 00:53:21,950
<i>That plant is indigenous to the island
which obtains seawater to grow.</i>

818
00:53:21,950 --> 00:53:26,490
<i>For some reason, it reacts to Devil Fruit eaters
and coils around them.</i>

819
00:53:26,930 --> 00:53:30,050
<i></i><i>The mechanism of it is unexplained but it's proven</i>

820
00:53:30,050 --> 00:53:34,210
<i>that it has the same effect as Sea Prism Stone.</i>

821
00:53:34,210 --> 00:53:40,050
<i></i><i>It's a very useful plant
for a normal person like me.</i>

822
00:53:40,050 --> 00:53:45,680
<i>Seems like you're looking for Nico Robin
but I've just been told that we caught her.</i>

823
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:46,620
What?!

824
00:53:46,940 --> 00:53:48,660
<i></i><i>You Devil Fruit eaters,</i>

825
00:53:48,660 --> 00:53:53,000
<i>especially the ones that are
running wild as pirates, tend to be overconfident...</i>

826
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:57,730
...about your own power.
You don't pay much attention to things around you.

827
00:53:57,730 --> 00:54:01,050
<i></i><i>It's a great strategy that seizes upon that weak point.</i>

828
00:54:01,050 --> 00:54:02,220
<i>It's called...</i>

829
00:54:02,280 --> 00:54:06,830
ANATHEMATIC SEA WHOLESALE ASSAULT MANEUVER

830
00:54:03,780 --> 00:54:06,110
"Anathematic Sea Wholesale Assault Maneuver"!

831
00:54:08,540 --> 00:54:13,670
There are more and more eye-popping secrets
to this island!

832
00:54:13,670 --> 00:54:17,580
They're so amazing and
Devil Fruit eaters have no chance against them!

833
00:54:19,750 --> 00:54:21,980
<i>The Worst Generation?</i>

834
00:54:21,980 --> 00:54:23,940
<i></i><i>The people who are depending on their</i>

835
00:54:23,940 --> 00:54:26,830
<i>ability become just helpless against a calculated plan!</i>

836
00:54:26,910 --> 00:54:30,890
I'll catch all of you way before the dawn!

837
00:54:30,890 --> 00:54:35,690
On the island that the god of the sea has given to us,
which kills the Devil Fruit eaters!

838
00:54:37,150 --> 00:54:41,630
<i>The island of fog - Nebulandia!</i>

839
00:54:44,240 --> 00:54:45,550
Hey, Straw Hat...

840
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:50,460
Oh, my Fear-of-unknown-islands-osis
is acting up!

841
00:54:50,450 --> 00:54:51,180
<i>Senpai</i>?

842
00:54:52,830 --> 00:54:54,310
The island of fog?

843
00:54:55,830 --> 00:55:00,380
I can't believe it...
I found myself getting emotional talking to them.

844
00:55:00,380 --> 00:55:01,550
It's not like me.

845
00:55:01,960 --> 00:55:07,510
No wonder.
We finally get to execute your plan.

846
00:55:07,510 --> 00:55:08,990
Yes, that's right.

847
00:55:09,290 --> 00:55:13,040
There were no other islands like this
which is exactly what I've been looking for.

848
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:15,890
I've always been thinking.

849
00:55:15,890 --> 00:55:18,510
How can we non Devil Fruit eaters

850
00:55:18,510 --> 00:55:22,320
capture the Devil Fruit eating pirates who act as they please?

851
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:27,090
Having plans wasn't enough.
We needed a geographical advantage, too.

852
00:55:28,120 --> 00:55:29,320
Yes!

853
00:55:29,730 --> 00:55:32,660
The island itself exercises
"Ability Nullification Maneuver"!

854
00:55:32,660 --> 00:55:34,790
ABILITY NULLIFICATION MANEUVER

855
00:55:34,790 --> 00:55:38,130
I chose this place as the field of the decisive battle against them.

856
00:55:38,720 --> 00:55:44,340
And they have been lured exactly as I designed.

857
00:55:45,130 --> 00:55:46,630
Why the sea?

858
00:55:46,630 --> 00:55:52,060
We Devil Fruit eaters have Devil Fruit powers
after eating Devil Fruits but in return,

859
00:55:52,060 --> 00:55:55,120
we risk being hated by sea.

860
00:55:55,270 --> 00:55:56,370
Being hated?

861
00:55:56,560 --> 00:56:00,670
They say Devil Fruits are the incarnations of
the Sea Devil so...

862
00:56:00,670 --> 00:56:04,400
...they can't move even a bit
under the influence of seawater.

863
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:09,260
That's why once they sink into it,
they'll never be able to come up.

864
00:56:09,260 --> 00:56:12,120
The whole island is like Sea Prism Stone.

865
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:13,830
Sea Prism Stone?

866
00:56:13,830 --> 00:56:16,960
It is said to be a stone
formed by the substance of seawater.

867
00:56:16,960 --> 00:56:18,210
What?! Then...

868
00:56:18,210 --> 00:56:21,630
For example, the handcuffs that
the Navy has are made of it.

869
00:56:21,630 --> 00:56:26,090
Since they have the same effect as seawater,
they nullify Devil Fruit eaters' powers.

870
00:56:26,090 --> 00:56:29,740
What?! That means
this island is very dangerous!

871
00:56:29,760 --> 00:56:33,230
He didn't kill Luffy in the Davy Back Fight because

872
00:56:33,230 --> 00:56:36,180
he wanted to take down all of us without fail.

873
00:56:36,180 --> 00:56:41,830
Locking up Zoro and Sanji, and disempowering
the Devil Fruit eaters gave him the advantage.

874
00:56:41,980 --> 00:56:43,790
Really, Navy?!

875
00:56:45,400 --> 00:56:46,960
So what?

876
00:56:46,990 --> 00:56:48,500
Fan guy!

877
00:56:49,110 --> 00:56:53,340
I won't leave this island
until I take back everybody!

878
00:57:04,960 --> 00:57:06,780
--Dammit!
--Luffy!

879
00:57:18,480 --> 00:57:21,650
--Stop!
--You stay still!

880
00:57:21,650 --> 00:57:22,870
That bastard!

881
00:57:23,330 --> 00:57:28,820
The more you move, the more you get hurt...
This is the worst island ever!

882
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:29,840
Damn!

883
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:35,240
<i>Senpai</i>! This is exactly when
sniping is needed!

884
00:57:35,240 --> 00:57:36,010
Okay!

885
00:57:38,790 --> 00:57:42,270
I'm gonna <i>super</i> show it off!

886
00:57:42,690 --> 00:57:45,560
Hey! Are you ready?!

887
00:57:45,590 --> 00:57:46,400
--Yes!
--Yeah!

888
00:57:46,920 --> 00:57:48,280
Go!

889
00:57:48,300 --> 00:57:50,190
Coup de Vent!

890
00:58:02,850 --> 00:58:03,670
Hey!

891
00:58:04,150 --> 00:58:06,670
Damn!
There are more and more of them!

892
00:58:06,770 --> 00:58:09,340
How about this?! Climate Baton!

893
00:58:11,860 --> 00:58:13,460
Black Ball!

894
00:58:25,130 --> 00:58:29,020
--A lightning conductor?!
--They're not gonna let it hit the tower, huh?!

895
00:58:33,300 --> 00:58:36,050
Judging from the situation here,
Chopper and Brook are probably...

896
00:58:36,050 --> 00:58:37,680
I guess.

897
00:58:42,230 --> 00:58:44,520
They got caught covering for us...

898
00:58:50,780 --> 00:58:53,570
Chuchun!
Take these two and get away!

899
00:58:53,570 --> 00:58:54,300
What?!

900
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:59,540
Leave them to us and find the Rebound Mushroom whatever it takes!

901
00:58:59,540 --> 00:59:01,040
Count on us!

902
00:59:06,170 --> 00:59:08,090
I gotta go back to save them!

903
00:59:12,760 --> 00:59:14,030
Look at that.

904
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:16,490
Sea Prism Stone handcuffs?

905
00:59:16,510 --> 00:59:21,060
When we get tied with those,
we can't use our abilities.

906
00:59:21,060 --> 00:59:25,230
That's why we have to prioritize
the Rebound Mushroom for now!

907
00:59:25,230 --> 00:59:26,210
Uh-huh!

908
00:59:32,940 --> 00:59:37,000
Wait for us! We'll definitely be back
to save you later!

909
00:59:54,210 --> 00:59:58,070
Vice Admiral Komei. You've got a call
from Vice Admiral Tsuru from HQ.

910
00:59:58,590 --> 01:00:01,140
Why it's Great Advisor-<i>dono</i>.

911
01:00:01,760 --> 01:00:03,620
How is everything going?

912
01:00:03,970 --> 01:00:08,120
I know you.
You must be having a great time, I guess.

913
01:00:04,640 --> 01:00:08,100
CLEAN JUSTICE

914
01:00:08,370 --> 01:00:10,360
Having a great time...

915
01:00:10,360 --> 01:00:15,010
The operation is going well
as I initially planned.

916
01:00:15,380 --> 01:00:20,050
<i>It should be.
Since I left so many troops in your hands.</i>

917
01:00:20,070 --> 01:00:24,330
The sun will set soon.
The decisive moment will be after the sunset.

918
01:00:24,330 --> 01:00:28,980
I'll bring nine heads of the Straw Hats
to you at any cost.

919
01:00:29,330 --> 01:00:30,460
Clank.

920
01:00:30,880 --> 01:00:34,340
We have to respond to
Great Advisor's expectations.

921
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:36,110
Don't be a fool.

922
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:41,620
Expectations or praise...
I have no interest in those flimsy things.

923
01:00:43,260 --> 01:00:48,140
Let's hunt down the remaining six.
Without a single mistake.

924
01:01:01,910 --> 01:01:03,950
I see...

925
01:01:05,540 --> 01:01:06,790
You jerk!

926
01:01:09,830 --> 01:01:13,730
We can go down underground
from where we blasted through.

927
01:01:13,750 --> 01:01:17,030
Underground? Can we get to the place
where Zoro and Sanji are like that?

928
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:21,480
I don't know about that.
There are a whole bunch of machines down there.

929
01:01:21,800 --> 01:01:27,660
Just saying maybe we can destroy
the system of those towers using that machinery.

930
01:01:27,680 --> 01:01:29,160
Alright! I'm going!

931
01:01:29,350 --> 01:01:31,810
It's filled with seawater.

932
01:01:32,480 --> 01:01:36,710
Seems like seawater is flowing into
the ground of this island.

933
01:01:36,730 --> 01:01:41,150
Oh, crap! This island is really unfavorable
for Devil Fruit eaters.

934
01:01:41,150 --> 01:01:43,870
We have no choice!
The two of us should do it!

935
01:01:43,870 --> 01:01:45,080
Count me in!

936
01:01:45,080 --> 01:01:47,950
Why don't you stay with your boss?

937
01:01:47,950 --> 01:01:49,770
What?! Just the two of you going?!

938
01:01:50,330 --> 01:01:52,980
Somebody capable must remain.
Otherwise, there'll be too much trouble.

939
01:01:54,040 --> 01:01:55,480
I got it!

940
01:01:55,810 --> 01:01:58,780
--Sorry. Could you hold these?
--Okay.

941
01:02:01,340 --> 01:02:02,660
So heavy!

942
01:02:02,840 --> 01:02:06,240
Wait for us, Luffy!
We'll find out where they are as well.

943
01:02:06,720 --> 01:02:07,610
Yeah.

944
01:02:07,970 --> 01:02:09,140
All right!

945
01:02:23,990 --> 01:02:25,450
Hm? Is it fog?

946
01:02:25,450 --> 01:02:28,060
That's because the temperature has dropped
after the sunset.

947
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:33,440
That's more like a geyser than a volcano.
That's why it's humid here.

948
01:02:39,670 --> 01:02:43,680
Chunchun-<i>san</i>...
I mean, Chuchun-<i>san</i>! Wake up!

949
01:02:58,230 --> 01:03:01,900
What's that? The mountain is wriggling!

950
01:03:01,900 --> 01:03:03,950
Chuchun, descend!

951
01:03:07,370 --> 01:03:09,990
It'll eat us and we'll be reduced to bones!

952
01:03:09,990 --> 01:03:12,250
But I'm already just bones...

953
01:03:17,580 --> 01:03:19,840
The moving mountain was actually...

954
01:03:19,840 --> 01:03:21,190
...Him.

955
01:03:21,710 --> 01:03:25,510
Brook, music!
Make him relax so we can help him!

956
01:03:25,510 --> 01:03:30,720
But, if I play,
it's like telling the Navy that we're here!

957
01:03:30,720 --> 01:03:32,470
I can't leave him like that!

958
01:03:35,700 --> 01:03:37,020
I understand.

959
01:03:37,020 --> 01:03:41,330
Okay then, listen to this.
A healing melody.

960
01:03:47,200 --> 01:03:48,740
Heavy Point!

961
01:03:54,330 --> 01:03:59,130
Don't worry! I'll save you at any cost!

962
01:04:10,010 --> 01:04:13,800
You can relax.
Chopper-<i>san</i> is a good doctor.

963
01:04:14,730 --> 01:04:17,810
It's gonna hurt a little but be patient!

964
01:04:21,440 --> 01:04:23,070
What's the matter?

965
01:04:23,070 --> 01:04:24,590
This smell!

966
01:04:29,360 --> 01:04:31,240
The Rebound Mushroom?!

967
01:04:31,240 --> 01:04:34,700
There they are!
The color and the shape match the image!

968
01:04:36,160 --> 01:04:37,900
Please be careful!

969
01:04:38,280 --> 01:04:42,060
I have a good idea!
I name him Mushroomconda!

970
01:04:43,980 --> 01:04:45,090
Mushroomconda...

971
01:04:45,090 --> 01:04:48,840
It has both the strangeness of mushrooms
and the dangerousness of giant creatures.

972
01:04:48,840 --> 01:04:50,070
It's a good name.

973
01:04:56,310 --> 01:04:56,950
Oh, no!

974
01:04:58,270 --> 01:05:02,960
I thought so!
My music has brought the Navy here!

975
01:05:15,660 --> 01:05:18,040
Isn't it getting sort of sticky?

976
01:05:18,040 --> 01:05:22,480
Am I imagining it?
The smell of the sea is getting stronger.

977
01:05:22,500 --> 01:05:23,870
The smell of the sea?

978
01:05:25,090 --> 01:05:30,030
I see! This fog formed because
the seawater underground got heated up!

979
01:05:30,050 --> 01:05:32,050
Seawater fog?

980
01:05:32,050 --> 01:05:36,220
Whatever it is, it's favorable for us.
We can hide ourselves.

981
01:05:36,220 --> 01:05:37,310
Yeah.

982
01:05:39,020 --> 01:05:42,980
What? But then,
is it the same as soaking in the sea?

983
01:05:42,980 --> 01:05:44,690
Luffy, are you okay?

984
01:05:44,690 --> 01:05:45,980
Oh, no...

985
01:05:46,730 --> 01:05:49,210
I'm totally losing my strength...

986
01:05:50,360 --> 01:05:51,950
Boss! Stay with me!

987
01:05:51,950 --> 01:05:55,970
How pathetic...
If I get attacked now, I'm finished.

988
01:05:55,970 --> 01:05:57,870
Don't say that.

989
01:05:57,870 --> 01:05:59,840
<i>Straw Hat Luffy.</i>

990
01:06:00,460 --> 01:06:02,480
<i>How do you feel?</i>

991
01:06:02,790 --> 01:06:08,960
<i>I think you're suffering
like you're in the sea now.</i>

992
01:06:08,960 --> 01:06:12,570
This is my second plan!
"Nighttime Fog Maneuver"!

993
01:06:12,590 --> 01:06:14,340
NIGHTTIME FOG MANEUVER

994
01:06:14,430 --> 01:06:16,600
Cut the maneuver crap!

995
01:06:21,730 --> 01:06:24,700
Nipple Light!

996
01:06:26,190 --> 01:06:28,730
That's gross! I don't like it!

997
01:06:35,410 --> 01:06:38,540
There is a reaction underground.
There are two people.

998
01:06:38,540 --> 01:06:40,500
Mm-hm. I knew they'd do that.

999
01:06:40,500 --> 01:06:42,080
Where are they now?

1000
01:06:42,080 --> 01:06:44,210
They're close to this operation room.

1001
01:06:44,210 --> 01:06:45,920
--Clank.
--Vice Admiral.

1002
01:06:45,920 --> 01:06:49,590
I just got a call from the detachment force
on the Mushroom Island.

1003
01:06:49,590 --> 01:06:53,380
He said they took custody of the ship doctor
and the musician from the Straw Hats,

1004
01:06:53,380 --> 01:06:57,140
and many from the Foxy Pirates
successfully.

1005
01:06:59,310 --> 01:07:03,040
It's all going as planned!
Announce to all soldiers!

1006
01:07:03,620 --> 01:07:08,020
We're moving on to the third plan!
We're entering the final phase at last!

1007
01:07:08,020 --> 01:07:10,150
--Yes, sir!
--Okay!

1008
01:07:17,970 --> 01:07:19,080
Oh, crap!

1009
01:07:30,170 --> 01:07:31,280
Franky!

1010
01:07:32,880 --> 01:07:34,820
What's that?!
Why is it glowing there?

1011
01:07:41,390 --> 01:07:45,290
You've gotta to be kidding!
Hey! Franky!

1012
01:07:52,070 --> 01:07:53,880
Komei, you bastard!

1013
01:07:53,880 --> 01:07:58,340
Even a cyborg can't get away from it.

1014
01:07:59,620 --> 01:08:00,950
Now,

1015
01:08:01,950 --> 01:08:05,790
you can't keep hanging there forever!

1016
01:08:06,620 --> 01:08:08,350
<i>Straw Hat Luffy!</i>

1017
01:08:09,630 --> 01:08:13,440
We got Cyborg Franky and Sniper King!

1018
01:08:14,260 --> 01:08:18,450
<i>Furthermore, we already placed the reindeer
and the skeleton under restraint, too!</i>

1019
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:21,260
Chopper and... Brook?

1020
01:08:23,270 --> 01:08:26,310
You literally can't do anything, can you?

1021
01:08:26,310 --> 01:08:31,250
Cat Burglar there is
the only friend you have left.

1022
01:08:31,270 --> 01:08:36,820
<i>Looks like you guys and I have
a big difference in power.</i>

1023
01:08:36,820 --> 01:08:41,260
<i>Thus, I'll change the rules a little bit.</i>

1024
01:08:41,260 --> 01:08:45,040
Change them?
I don't like the way you talk down to us!

1025
01:08:46,540 --> 01:08:53,130
<i>It's still before sunrise
but I'll take all of your captured friends outside.</i>

1026
01:08:53,130 --> 01:08:56,900
<i>In exchange for that,
I want you to come get them on your own!</i>

1027
01:08:57,130 --> 01:08:59,930
What?! Are you playing a game or something?!

1028
01:08:59,930 --> 01:09:04,170
<i>Are you in or not?! Just state it clearly!</i>

1029
01:09:04,640 --> 01:09:07,120
Hey! What about Porche and Hamburg?!

1030
01:09:07,230 --> 01:09:10,980
<i>If you can make it
before the sun rises above the horizon,</i>

1031
01:09:10,980 --> 01:09:14,610
<i>you can trade yourself for your friends.</i>

1032
01:09:14,610 --> 01:09:16,680
I said "What about my friends?!"

1033
01:09:17,130 --> 01:09:22,580
<i>If you can't make it, your friends will be sent to Impel Down as arranged!</i>

1034
01:09:23,830 --> 01:09:25,400
<i>Are you in?</i>

1035
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:27,020
Luffy...

1036
01:09:27,500 --> 01:09:31,270
I'm not gonna let you have my friends!

1037
01:09:31,380 --> 01:09:32,350
Luffy...

1038
01:09:36,590 --> 01:09:40,200
Good. Then, let's begin!

1039
01:09:40,590 --> 01:09:42,060
He ignored me...

1040
01:09:45,930 --> 01:09:47,020
Hey!

1041
01:09:49,230 --> 01:09:53,080
Split-Head!
I'll bring your friends back, too!

1042
01:09:54,900 --> 01:09:56,360
Luffy!

1043
01:09:58,110 --> 01:10:00,340
I'm okay! I'll go by myself!

1044
01:10:03,870 --> 01:10:05,160
Luffy!

1045
01:10:11,790 --> 01:10:13,520
Straw Hat...

1046
01:10:28,270 --> 01:10:33,400
I can't believe this. The formidable Straw Hats
have been brought down this easily...

1047
01:10:33,400 --> 01:10:36,890
Boss! We can't let Straw Hat go alone!

1048
01:10:37,770 --> 01:10:38,980
Hey!

1049
01:10:38,980 --> 01:10:42,610
I don't think that dirty Komei
will fight him so straightforwardly!

1050
01:10:42,610 --> 01:10:43,840
Wait a sec!

1051
01:10:43,990 --> 01:10:48,060
It's our turn to help Straw Hat
who brought us here!

1052
01:10:48,160 --> 01:10:49,560
You...

1053
01:10:49,580 --> 01:10:52,430
--<i>Kancho</i> is right!
--It's KanSHO!

1054
01:10:52,430 --> 01:10:55,170
Split-Head!
Try your best and pay back your debt!

1055
01:10:55,170 --> 01:10:56,560
Still calling me that?!

1056
01:11:31,580 --> 01:11:32,350
Zoro!

1057
01:11:32,620 --> 01:11:33,480
Sanji!

1058
01:11:33,910 --> 01:11:34,890
Robin!

1059
01:11:35,040 --> 01:11:36,270
Franky!

1060
01:11:36,500 --> 01:11:37,780
Usopp!

1061
01:11:37,780 --> 01:11:38,860
Luffy!

1062
01:11:38,960 --> 01:11:40,050
Everybody!

1063
01:11:40,050 --> 01:11:41,860
L-Luffy! It's a trap!

1064
01:11:42,300 --> 01:11:44,150
Don't come closer...

1065
01:11:44,170 --> 01:11:46,430
I'll save you now!

1066
01:11:46,430 --> 01:11:50,910
Are you on your own?
Where's Nami?! And the others?!

1067
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:52,770
No...

1068
01:11:52,770 --> 01:11:54,040
S-Stay away...

1069
01:11:54,140 --> 01:11:56,190
I'm sure it's a trap!

1070
01:11:56,190 --> 01:11:57,290
I know...

1071
01:12:00,520 --> 01:12:01,860
Luffy!

1072
01:12:05,240 --> 01:12:06,780
L-Luffy!

1073
01:12:09,370 --> 01:12:12,620
Sorry that I'm late.

1074
01:12:12,620 --> 01:12:18,420
Let's get off of this annoying island already
and go on an adventure again, all nine of us!

1075
01:12:18,420 --> 01:12:20,500
Hang on!

1076
01:12:20,500 --> 01:12:24,280
I'll save you right now!!

1077
01:12:25,220 --> 01:12:27,510
--What an idiot...
--Luffy...

1078
01:12:28,890 --> 01:12:31,740
Yeah, that's right! Just save us already!

1079
01:12:36,100 --> 01:12:36,910
Luffy!

1080
01:12:38,100 --> 01:12:40,130
That was close...

1081
01:12:42,480 --> 01:12:44,610
Luffy! Don't fall!

1082
01:12:44,610 --> 01:12:46,030
Yeah!

1083
01:12:51,280 --> 01:12:52,870
Hey! Luffy!

1084
01:12:52,870 --> 01:12:56,850
I feel weaker than before...

1085
01:13:01,920 --> 01:13:03,110
He's...

1086
01:13:03,590 --> 01:13:07,130
A hidden pitfall is my most favorite trap.

1087
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:12,680
Although it's the simplest trap
that mankind has ever invented,

1088
01:13:12,680 --> 01:13:15,040
it's very effective.

1089
01:13:16,810 --> 01:13:18,040
It's called...

1090
01:13:18,100 --> 01:13:22,230
CREWMATE PITFALL MANEUVER

1091
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:22,250
..."Crewmate Pitfall Maneuver"!

1092
01:13:22,560 --> 01:13:27,550
The fact you think a great deal of your friends
will bring about your own death!

1093
01:13:27,570 --> 01:13:29,660
There is seawater down there.

1094
01:13:29,660 --> 01:13:31,490
Oh, that's why...

1095
01:13:31,490 --> 01:13:35,640
It's quite simple but there is
a thick darkness of fear.

1096
01:13:36,620 --> 01:13:37,980
You jerk...

1097
01:13:39,750 --> 01:13:41,750
Are you terrified?

1098
01:13:42,420 --> 01:13:46,860
When I was a child,
I experienced bigger terror.

1099
01:13:47,260 --> 01:13:51,990
The ones that made me terrified were
none other than pirates!

1100
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:55,620
They rampaged through my home town.

1101
01:13:55,620 --> 01:13:58,420
It was such a hideous tragedy that I could hardly bear to look at!

1102
01:13:59,230 --> 01:14:01,520
Pirates are evil!

1103
01:14:01,520 --> 01:14:03,270
You see?!

1104
01:14:03,270 --> 01:14:08,360
I joined the Navy to fight against evil
and eradicate it! But...

1105
01:14:09,650 --> 01:14:12,030
...I couldn't believe it!

1106
01:14:12,030 --> 01:14:17,900
Both the World Government and the Navy
tolerate pirates for the maintenance of order!

1107
01:14:18,500 --> 01:14:24,330
People at higher levels can't see how ordinary people are
living under threat of...

1108
01:14:24,330 --> 01:14:26,500
...the violence of pirates!

1109
01:14:26,800 --> 01:14:29,940
The era of violence will never end like this!

1110
01:14:30,420 --> 01:14:34,640
Because they're trying to counter
violence with violence!

1111
01:14:34,640 --> 01:14:39,340
Does it mean powerless people
can't do anything?!

1112
01:14:39,850 --> 01:14:45,150
Nay! There is a weapon to fight back!
A weapon called wisdom!

1113
01:14:45,150 --> 01:14:49,530
With my wisdom, I'll bring an end to
this era of the cycle of violence!

1114
01:14:49,530 --> 01:14:53,970
That will give hope to powerless people!

1115
01:14:54,450 --> 01:14:58,540
To accomplish that,
I'll even reform the Navy!

1116
01:14:58,540 --> 01:15:02,730
You people are sacrifices
for the ray of hope!

1117
01:15:04,750 --> 01:15:06,380
Luffy!

1118
01:15:07,590 --> 01:15:10,080
You knew something like this would happen to you!

1119
01:15:10,080 --> 01:15:12,860
Then, why would you wanna become a pirate?

1120
01:15:13,180 --> 01:15:16,320
I don't understand
what you people are thinking.

1121
01:15:17,470 --> 01:15:19,580
It's your loss!

1122
01:15:20,560 --> 01:15:23,450
That you don't know the adventures
we're having!

1123
01:15:25,900 --> 01:15:28,190
So what?

1124
01:15:28,190 --> 01:15:32,440
Pirates can seek adventures freely!

1125
01:15:32,440 --> 01:15:34,910
Across the vast extent of the sea!

1126
01:15:37,240 --> 01:15:38,780
I understand.

1127
01:15:38,780 --> 01:15:42,810
The fact that
it's impossible to understand you.

1128
01:15:45,840 --> 01:15:46,900
Luffy!

1129
01:15:56,550 --> 01:15:58,530
The way you hang onto your life!

1130
01:15:59,300 --> 01:16:01,290
I admire that.

1131
01:16:03,560 --> 01:16:04,810
Oh... Oh, no!

1132
01:16:04,810 --> 01:16:05,710
That's...

1133
01:16:05,730 --> 01:16:07,070
Haki?!

1134
01:16:15,400 --> 01:16:16,880
H-He's dancing!

1135
01:16:18,120 --> 01:16:20,280
The Haki of the Color of Arms!

1136
01:16:20,280 --> 01:16:22,190
With that spirit of mine,

1137
01:16:23,580 --> 01:16:26,850
I apply power to my fan!

1138
01:16:40,760 --> 01:16:42,760
Is that for real?!

1139
01:16:43,100 --> 01:16:44,430
Now,

1140
01:16:45,850 --> 01:16:50,460
out of respect for your tenacity,
I'll finish you off myself.

1141
01:16:51,020 --> 01:16:52,880
Push you with this sword and...

1142
01:16:53,860 --> 01:16:59,890
...I will watch you sink down to your end
with my own two eyes!

1143
01:17:00,700 --> 01:17:02,510
Don't do it!!

1144
01:17:04,200 --> 01:17:06,020
Luffy!!

1145
01:17:18,930 --> 01:17:20,360
Heat Egg!

1146
01:17:22,140 --> 01:17:24,410
--Oh, Nami-<i>san</i>!
--Ow, ow, ow, ow...

1147
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:25,790
The fog is clearing!

1148
01:17:27,770 --> 01:17:29,080
Everybody! Oh!

1149
01:17:29,190 --> 01:17:31,020
--You came!
--Nami!

1150
01:17:31,100 --> 01:17:32,080
Where's Luffy?!

1151
01:17:32,080 --> 01:17:34,530
In the seawater
in the pitfall right there!

1152
01:17:34,530 --> 01:17:35,440
What?!

1153
01:17:35,650 --> 01:17:36,550
Look up!

1154
01:17:42,160 --> 01:17:44,220
Luffy!!

1155
01:17:45,660 --> 01:17:47,930
I'm counting on you, Nami! Save Luffy...

1156
01:17:50,140 --> 01:17:51,310
Nami!

1157
01:17:51,750 --> 01:17:53,150
Nami!

1158
01:17:54,630 --> 01:17:55,710
Hey.

1159
01:17:55,710 --> 01:17:58,470
If you move even a bit,
I'll blow your head off.

1160
01:17:58,470 --> 01:18:00,900
--Good job, you!
--Yeah!

1161
01:18:00,900 --> 01:18:03,680
Be careful! He uses Haki!

1162
01:18:03,680 --> 01:18:06,370
When the fog is clear,
we have the upper hand.

1163
01:18:07,310 --> 01:18:12,480
Get away from the hole. Slowly.
Don't do anything foolish.

1164
01:18:12,480 --> 01:18:14,400
Yeah, good boy!

1165
01:18:18,820 --> 01:18:21,110
Where are my friends?!

1166
01:18:21,110 --> 01:18:23,190
Look for them yourself.

1167
01:18:23,700 --> 01:18:25,970
--Kansho, hold this.
--Okay!

1168
01:18:27,330 --> 01:18:30,520
--Hey! Help Nami!
--Okay!

1169
01:18:34,670 --> 01:18:36,710
Hold onto it tight!

1170
01:18:36,710 --> 01:18:38,170
Pull me up!

1171
01:18:42,760 --> 01:18:44,600
--Nami!
--Ow, ow!

1172
01:18:44,600 --> 01:18:45,950
Is Luffy okay?!

1173
01:18:46,050 --> 01:18:47,280
He isn't breathing!

1174
01:18:47,390 --> 01:18:49,040
--What?!
--Luffy!

1175
01:18:49,040 --> 01:18:50,660
Oh, damn!

1176
01:18:51,140 --> 01:18:53,730
Hey! Wake up!

1177
01:18:54,770 --> 01:18:57,130
Hey! Hey!

1178
01:19:00,110 --> 01:19:01,610
Wake up!

1179
01:19:01,780 --> 01:19:03,250
Straw Hat!

1180
01:19:04,320 --> 01:19:05,560
Luffy!

1181
01:19:05,820 --> 01:19:08,620
Wake up!!

1182
01:19:08,620 --> 01:19:10,000
Luffy...

1183
01:19:10,000 --> 01:19:12,450
Wake up! Wake up!

1184
01:19:15,880 --> 01:19:18,090
Hey! Just wake up already,
Straw Hat!

1185
01:19:18,090 --> 01:19:21,530
You said you're gonna become
the King of the Pirates!

1186
01:19:21,550 --> 01:19:23,050
Luffy...

1187
01:19:23,050 --> 01:19:24,030
Ouch!

1188
01:19:28,720 --> 01:19:30,520
--Luffy!
--Oh, good...

1189
01:19:31,770 --> 01:19:34,870
--You scared me!
--Yeah...

1190
01:19:36,060 --> 01:19:37,400
Everybody!

1191
01:19:38,020 --> 01:19:39,960
--Let's get off of this island!
--Uh-huh!

1192
01:19:40,690 --> 01:19:41,760
Yeah!

1193
01:19:41,860 --> 01:19:44,400
Together with Split-Head's friends!

1194
01:19:44,400 --> 01:19:45,430
Straw Hat!

1195
01:20:01,760 --> 01:20:02,870
Hey...

1196
01:20:07,760 --> 01:20:10,200
No... Luffy...

1197
01:20:10,760 --> 01:20:13,380
Luffy!!

1198
01:20:14,770 --> 01:20:16,170
H-He is...

1199
01:20:19,480 --> 01:20:20,860
Kansho!

1200
01:20:21,360 --> 01:20:24,880
Did you... Did you shoot him?!

1201
01:20:26,740 --> 01:20:27,660
It's called...

1202
01:20:27,660 --> 01:20:31,620
TWO-SIDED BACKSTAB MANEUVER

1203
01:20:28,950 --> 01:20:31,100
..."Two-sided Backstab Maneuver"!

1204
01:20:31,660 --> 01:20:35,980
When someone turns his back on his ally,
it's the best chance to attack!

1205
01:20:36,330 --> 01:20:40,110
He lowered his guard for a while
when he got out of the pitfall safely.

1206
01:20:40,130 --> 01:20:44,490
That moment was what I was looking for
to take a sure shot!

1207
01:20:44,490 --> 01:20:46,700
Boss. <i>Senpai</i>.

1208
01:20:47,080 --> 01:20:50,240
I'm sorry! But this is my job!

1209
01:20:50,930 --> 01:20:51,810
JUSTICE

1210
01:21:01,730 --> 01:21:03,420
You bastard!

1211
01:21:03,860 --> 01:21:08,720
Wake up, Luffy!
Bullets don't harm you! Right?! Hey!

1212
01:21:08,820 --> 01:21:10,700
Wake up, Luffy!

1213
01:21:10,700 --> 01:21:12,690
It's unforgivable...

1214
01:21:12,830 --> 01:21:14,430
Screw you!

1215
01:21:14,580 --> 01:21:16,770
Thunder Lance Tempo!

1216
01:21:25,720 --> 01:21:27,190
--Arrest them!
--Yes, sir!

1217
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:39,600
Whoa-whoa-whoa!

1218
01:21:44,940 --> 01:21:46,610
--Nami!
--Don't move!

1219
01:21:47,360 --> 01:21:49,680
I-I'm losing my strength...

1220
01:21:52,030 --> 01:21:53,720
I won!

1221
01:21:54,030 --> 01:21:59,090
Look! The man with a 400 million berry bounty
who heads the list of the Worst Generation,

1222
01:21:59,090 --> 01:22:02,940
Straw Hat and all of his crew are
in our custody!

1223
01:22:02,940 --> 01:22:06,980
It's our complete victory!

1224
01:22:17,060 --> 01:22:20,310
You did it, Komei-<i>kakka</i>.

1225
01:22:20,310 --> 01:22:22,400
The capture of the Straw Hats!

1226
01:22:22,400 --> 01:22:26,480
This is no less the beginning of
the end of the Pirate Era!

1227
01:22:26,480 --> 01:22:28,280
That's right!

1228
01:22:28,280 --> 01:22:33,490
The formidable Komei-<i>kakka</i>!
His name resounds all over the great sea!

1229
01:22:33,490 --> 01:22:38,930
The formidable Komei-<i>kakka</i>!
His name resounds all over the great sea!

1230
01:22:38,950 --> 01:22:43,460
The formidable Komei-<i>kakka</i>!
His name resounds all over the great sea!

1231
01:22:43,710 --> 01:22:46,260
I will have your skills!

1232
01:22:46,260 --> 01:22:47,610
--Dojaku!
--Yes, sir!

1233
01:22:47,910 --> 01:22:51,010
We'll take all seven of them
to the Navy Headquarters!

1234
01:22:51,010 --> 01:22:53,200
--Make preparations now!
--Got it!

1235
01:22:54,050 --> 01:22:55,620
Activate!

1236
01:23:10,360 --> 01:23:14,400
Look at that, you damn pirates!
I, Dojaku the genius, made...

1237
01:23:14,400 --> 01:23:17,490
...the greatest gimmick of my life!

1238
01:23:33,920 --> 01:23:35,360
A mushroom?! A snake?!

1239
01:23:38,660 --> 01:23:41,040
--Luffy!
--Boss!

1240
01:23:41,480 --> 01:23:42,660
You guys...

1241
01:23:43,520 --> 01:23:46,630
--I thought we captured them!
--Oh, great!

1242
01:23:47,810 --> 01:23:49,000
I'm here!

1243
01:23:49,270 --> 01:23:50,590
You're okay!

1244
01:23:50,690 --> 01:23:51,810
How annoying!

1245
01:24:01,370 --> 01:24:02,980
Awesome!

1246
01:24:03,680 --> 01:24:06,290
--Everybody, help me!
--Yeah!

1247
01:24:08,460 --> 01:24:10,230
Kung Fu Point!

1248
01:24:15,380 --> 01:24:16,550
Brook!

1249
01:24:16,550 --> 01:24:18,340
Sorry to keep you waiting.

1250
01:24:44,370 --> 01:24:46,690
All of you, charge!

1251
01:24:59,010 --> 01:25:01,780
Take this!
The powder of the Sneeze Mushroom!

1252
01:25:03,020 --> 01:25:04,410
Yeah, yeah!

1253
01:25:26,160 --> 01:25:29,000
M-My greatest gimmick!

1254
01:25:29,000 --> 01:25:31,480
I couldn't even unveil it!

1255
01:25:39,590 --> 01:25:41,110
I'm free!

1256
01:25:41,110 --> 01:25:42,320
--Here you go!
--Thank you!

1257
01:25:45,310 --> 01:25:49,080
--You're not hurt, are you?
--Thank you! You're kind.

1258
01:25:49,080 --> 01:25:51,860
--W-Well...
--Take care of Franky, too.

1259
01:25:51,860 --> 01:25:52,880
My pleasure!

1260
01:25:53,770 --> 01:25:55,570
--Brook!
--Sanji!

1261
01:25:55,570 --> 01:25:58,150
Hey, I thought you got captured.

1262
01:25:58,150 --> 01:25:59,530
That was a lie!

1263
01:26:00,110 --> 01:26:02,630
I was the one who called them.

1264
01:26:02,990 --> 01:26:07,750
If I told him that,
he'll lower his guard, I thought!

1265
01:26:07,750 --> 01:26:10,770
And Mushroomconda is a good boy!

1266
01:26:10,790 --> 01:26:16,550
After I made medicine out of
the Rebound Mushrooms, he carried us here!

1267
01:26:16,550 --> 01:26:19,680
Drink this. It's a component of the Rebound Mushroom.

1268
01:26:19,950 --> 01:26:21,390
Here, drink it.

1269
01:26:22,050 --> 01:26:24,780
Somebody, uncuff me, too.

1270
01:26:25,010 --> 01:26:26,700
Boss!

1271
01:26:26,810 --> 01:26:27,540
Here's the key!

1272
01:26:29,980 --> 01:26:32,790
I'm back!

1273
01:26:36,980 --> 01:26:39,970
These are the ampules
for Porche and Hamburg.

1274
01:26:39,970 --> 01:26:41,260
Oh, great!

1275
01:26:41,990 --> 01:26:44,470
I feel like I was having a nightmare.

1276
01:26:44,470 --> 01:26:46,310
--He's back!
--Yes!

1277
01:26:46,310 --> 01:26:47,450
Sanji!

1278
01:26:47,910 --> 01:26:50,270
Now I'm free!

1279
01:26:50,560 --> 01:26:52,120
--He's back!
--Uh-huh!

1280
01:26:52,120 --> 01:26:53,290
Yeah!

1281
01:26:59,800 --> 01:27:01,650
All right. Let's do it!

1282
01:27:02,040 --> 01:27:03,860
I gotta create some havoc.

1283
01:27:03,860 --> 01:27:06,140
Pirate Hunter, take these!

1284
01:27:08,350 --> 01:27:10,830
Thank you, Split-Head!

1285
01:27:10,830 --> 01:27:13,210
You call me that even now?

1286
01:27:13,210 --> 01:27:15,380
You need these, don't you?!

1287
01:27:17,020 --> 01:27:20,990
<i>Super</i> big comeback!

1288
01:27:21,820 --> 01:27:22,740
Luffy!

1289
01:27:22,740 --> 01:27:26,100
--He got shot by Kansho!
--What?!

1290
01:27:26,460 --> 01:27:30,110
You're made of rubber so they don't harm you, right?!
Wake up! Luffy!

1291
01:27:30,110 --> 01:27:31,140
Is this for real?

1292
01:27:31,250 --> 01:27:35,210
Oh, if we could've gotten here
a little sooner...

1293
01:27:35,210 --> 01:27:37,790
Oh, boy... It's too late.

1294
01:27:37,790 --> 01:27:40,050
You couldn't turn it around.

1295
01:27:40,050 --> 01:27:42,360
This is how it was supposed to be.

1296
01:27:42,470 --> 01:27:43,570
That bastard!

1297
01:27:46,550 --> 01:27:47,530
It's my voice?!

1298
01:27:48,350 --> 01:27:49,350
What?

1299
01:27:51,480 --> 01:27:53,120
Oh, I surprised myself!

1300
01:27:53,230 --> 01:27:55,160
You surprised us!

1301
01:27:55,620 --> 01:27:57,500
What?! I knew I didn't miss!

1302
01:28:01,360 --> 01:28:03,220
H-He has the devil's luck!

1303
01:28:05,860 --> 01:28:08,300
Split-Head, sorry. It's broken...

1304
01:28:08,330 --> 01:28:10,410
I really liked it...

1305
01:28:10,410 --> 01:28:11,930
You really liked it?!

1306
01:28:12,500 --> 01:28:13,500
Dammit!

1307
01:28:15,750 --> 01:28:17,920
That's impressive!

1308
01:28:18,840 --> 01:28:19,880
No way!

1309
01:28:19,880 --> 01:28:21,460
You traitor!

1310
01:28:21,460 --> 01:28:23,920
Nine-tails Rush!

1311
01:28:26,510 --> 01:28:28,130
You're next!

1312
01:28:32,100 --> 01:28:33,910
--Foxy!
--Boss!

1313
01:28:34,020 --> 01:28:35,250
Stay still!

1314
01:28:37,770 --> 01:28:39,060
Boss!

1315
01:28:39,060 --> 01:28:41,500
--You okay?!
--Don't push yourself.

1316
01:28:41,500 --> 01:28:44,220
Thank you, Big Sis... I mean, lady.

1317
01:28:44,530 --> 01:28:47,410
Don't mention it.
It's just payback for what you did earlier.

1318
01:28:47,410 --> 01:28:49,030
Lady...?

1319
01:28:49,030 --> 01:28:49,890
Never mind.

1320
01:28:53,910 --> 01:28:55,080
Guys!

1321
01:28:55,080 --> 01:28:56,620
Let's get off of this island!

1322
01:28:56,620 --> 01:28:57,390
Yeah!

1323
01:28:57,540 --> 01:28:59,910
Hey, Split-Head Fox-taro!

1324
01:28:59,910 --> 01:29:01,000
Who are you calling?!

1325
01:29:01,000 --> 01:29:03,050
Your friends are in there.

1326
01:29:03,050 --> 01:29:06,180
That tower, huh?! Thanks, great cook!

1327
01:29:06,180 --> 01:29:07,970
--Let's go!
--Yeah!

1328
01:29:07,970 --> 01:29:11,220
Pickles! Big Bun!
You take care of stuff here!

1329
01:29:11,220 --> 01:29:11,990
Yeah!

1330
01:29:17,850 --> 01:29:19,380
Oni... Giri!

1331
01:29:27,060 --> 01:29:30,570
You have such amazing survival power
and the devil's luck. I'm impressed.

1332
01:29:30,570 --> 01:29:36,730
I thought I was being cautious enough
but your friends totally got the better of me.

1333
01:29:37,040 --> 01:29:43,250
But this isn't over yet!
You're still in my hands!

1334
01:29:43,250 --> 01:29:46,740
I won't let you escape!
You can't get out of here alive...

1335
01:29:46,740 --> 01:29:47,700
Heat Egg!

1336
01:29:55,810 --> 01:29:57,640
How do you like it?

1337
01:29:57,640 --> 01:30:00,170
It's called "Flare Maneuver"!

1338
01:30:00,190 --> 01:30:01,060
FLARE MANEUVER

1339
01:30:01,980 --> 01:30:04,290
Your taste is nowhere near mine!

1340
01:30:04,400 --> 01:30:07,190
Forget it!
I'm not good at those things!

1341
01:30:07,190 --> 01:30:08,570
I won't forgive evil!

1342
01:30:08,570 --> 01:30:13,360
So that people can get serenity
and everlasting peace!

1343
01:30:24,090 --> 01:30:24,940
Oh, no!

1344
01:30:25,170 --> 01:30:26,760
The outer rim is...!

1345
01:30:29,420 --> 01:30:32,660
This basin is below sea level.

1346
01:30:32,680 --> 01:30:37,120
I didn't want to use this last strategy
but I had no choice.

1347
01:30:37,350 --> 01:30:39,350
He gave up the Navy base!

1348
01:30:39,350 --> 01:30:41,210
--Nami, take everybody!
--Uh-huh!

1349
01:30:41,350 --> 01:30:44,540
Bang! Bang! Bang!

1350
01:30:52,200 --> 01:30:54,280
The seawater keeps pouring in!

1351
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:57,470
Tsk! He won't stop targeting
Devil Fruit eaters!

1352
01:30:57,470 --> 01:30:58,350
It's here!

1353
01:30:58,540 --> 01:31:00,980
I'm gonna create more and more havoc!

1354
01:31:00,980 --> 01:31:04,000
Haven't had enough
for the humiliation I bore!

1355
01:31:04,000 --> 01:31:07,520
Both of you, wrap it up.
We'll leave the rest to Luffy!

1356
01:31:09,380 --> 01:31:11,720
It's so spectacular!

1357
01:31:11,720 --> 01:31:17,390
Fan guy! This is a Navy base, isn't it?
They'll get mad at you, won't they?

1358
01:31:17,390 --> 01:31:21,330
They will.
But that's none of your concern.

1359
01:31:21,690 --> 01:31:27,190
I'll take any punishment!
If I can capture the Straw Hats,

1360
01:31:27,190 --> 01:31:28,500
I can't ask for more!

1361
01:31:29,070 --> 01:31:33,430
Seems like I really can't get out of here
without taking you down.

1362
01:31:33,610 --> 01:31:35,680
Let's make a dash for the Sunny!

1363
01:31:45,220 --> 01:31:45,980
Already here?!

1364
01:31:50,130 --> 01:31:52,770
You're quite off, aren't you?

1365
01:31:52,770 --> 01:31:55,530
--Not as bad as your pervy eyebrows.
--Hurry up!

1366
01:31:57,720 --> 01:32:00,490
Beam! Beam!

1367
01:32:01,350 --> 01:32:03,910
Beam! Beam!

1368
01:32:04,520 --> 01:32:08,090
Slow-Slow-Beam! Slower! Slower!

1369
01:32:10,190 --> 01:32:12,460
Slow-Slow Beam!

1370
01:32:15,860 --> 01:32:17,860
Porche! Hamburg!

1371
01:32:18,410 --> 01:32:19,740
Are you okay?!

1372
01:32:19,740 --> 01:32:21,500
Boss...?

1373
01:32:22,200 --> 01:32:24,810
Sorry to keep you waiting!
I'm here to save you!

1374
01:32:25,070 --> 01:32:27,580
He came all the way?

1375
01:32:29,420 --> 01:32:31,550
Boss!

1376
01:32:31,550 --> 01:32:34,930
Oh, I'm sorry that
you had to go through this.

1377
01:32:34,930 --> 01:32:37,090
--We don't have time!
--You're right.

1378
01:32:37,090 --> 01:32:40,060
You guys, drink this. Here.

1379
01:32:42,720 --> 01:32:44,960
Ooh! I'm back!

1380
01:32:44,960 --> 01:32:47,020
--There they are!
--Catch them!

1381
01:32:47,020 --> 01:32:49,360
Slow-Slow Beam!

1382
01:32:49,360 --> 01:32:50,460
Again?!

1383
01:32:51,900 --> 01:32:54,510
--Oh, he moves!
--You bastards!

1384
01:32:54,570 --> 01:32:55,720
Shut up!

1385
01:32:55,720 --> 01:33:00,080
What's going on out there?
They took the three of them somewhere...

1386
01:33:00,080 --> 01:33:03,810
Straw Hat is fighting outside!
They're wreaking havoc together!

1387
01:33:03,800 --> 01:33:06,170
Now, we gotta get out of here!

1388
01:33:06,170 --> 01:33:08,210
Boss, you can go ahead.

1389
01:33:09,170 --> 01:33:11,820
There's something we want to
take back at any price!

1390
01:33:11,920 --> 01:33:13,380
What is it?!

1391
01:33:13,380 --> 01:33:15,690
We'll catch up on you in a bit.

1392
01:33:17,130 --> 01:33:19,920
Hey! I took the trouble to save you...

1393
01:33:20,970 --> 01:33:23,850
You guys can go ahead and run!
I'll look after them...

1394
01:33:23,850 --> 01:33:25,520
What are you talking about?

1395
01:33:26,070 --> 01:33:30,210
We're friends! We'll stay with you
even to the nethermost hell!

1396
01:33:30,690 --> 01:33:32,880
You guys...

1397
01:33:34,740 --> 01:33:38,430
Now you can't exercise
all your power again.

1398
01:33:38,950 --> 01:33:42,030
It's better for you to get caught
without resistance.

1399
01:33:42,030 --> 01:33:46,140
I'll get out of here after I get my friends back.
Don't make me repeat myself!

1400
01:33:46,360 --> 01:33:48,980
Enough with your lip!

1401
01:33:52,710 --> 01:33:54,090
Gum-Gum...

1402
01:33:54,090 --> 01:33:55,770
...Pistol!

1403
01:33:56,490 --> 01:33:57,860
Double shot!

1404
01:33:59,470 --> 01:34:01,220
Stamp!

1405
01:34:08,020 --> 01:34:09,330
That was close!

1406
01:34:09,940 --> 01:34:11,540
How tenacious.

1407
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:16,090
But you're obviously moving slow.

1408
01:34:19,360 --> 01:34:21,390
I'll never come back to an island like this!

1409
01:34:39,550 --> 01:34:42,110
Your time is up, literally.

1410
01:34:43,680 --> 01:34:45,850
The water has stopped rising?

1411
01:34:45,850 --> 01:34:47,850
Oh, Choppy!

1412
01:34:48,600 --> 01:34:52,480
--You two made it out, too.
--Hey, let's get out of here quick!

1413
01:34:52,480 --> 01:34:55,250
Hey, Straw Hats!
What in the world is going on here?

1414
01:34:55,250 --> 01:34:56,650
Oh, no!

1415
01:34:56,650 --> 01:35:01,050
Oh! Wait, I've got a good...
I mean, a bad idea!

1416
01:35:01,050 --> 01:35:04,350
Hey, Cyborg! Carry me on your shoulder!

1417
01:35:18,800 --> 01:35:21,990
Yo! I found a good place to stand!

1418
01:35:23,340 --> 01:35:27,060
Quit life as a pirate and go join a circus!

1419
01:35:33,350 --> 01:35:35,730
Slow-Slow Beam!

1420
01:35:38,150 --> 01:35:39,880
--Split-Head!
--You...

1421
01:35:39,370 --> 01:35:42,570
Slow-Slow Beam!

1422
01:35:42,570 --> 01:35:45,050
How did you like it, you fool?!

1423
01:35:45,050 --> 01:35:47,390
Hey! Hit the bullet all you want!

1424
01:35:47,870 --> 01:35:52,140
Even though you got weaker by the seawater,
if you go "more-more" like I do,

1425
01:35:52,140 --> 01:35:53,830
you can be very powerful!

1426
01:35:53,830 --> 01:35:56,960
Your head is split but you're smart!

1427
01:35:56,960 --> 01:35:57,920
Okay!

1428
01:36:00,550 --> 01:36:03,070
Alright, is it good now?
Let's go to the ship!

1429
01:36:03,760 --> 01:36:06,720
More! More, more, more, more!

1430
01:36:06,720 --> 01:36:09,450
More, more, more, more! More, more, more!

1431
01:36:09,810 --> 01:36:11,680
Choppy!

1432
01:36:12,060 --> 01:36:14,870
More, more, more, more, more, more, more!

1433
01:36:17,150 --> 01:36:18,770
30 seconds!

1434
01:36:20,150 --> 01:36:21,400
It's hot!

1435
01:36:28,620 --> 01:36:30,240
The water's draining!

1436
01:36:30,240 --> 01:36:31,960
He did it!

1437
01:36:39,130 --> 01:36:41,440
Gum-Gum Pitfall!

1438
01:36:42,170 --> 01:36:42,860
What?!

1439
01:36:43,420 --> 01:36:45,920
You love pitfalls, don't you?

1440
01:36:46,550 --> 01:36:49,810
You've been taking Split-Head for a fool,
haven't you?

1441
01:36:49,810 --> 01:36:52,870
How does it feel like to be brought down
by such a guy?

1442
01:36:53,230 --> 01:36:56,120
The seawater's gone now! Here I go!

1443
01:36:56,140 --> 01:36:58,710
Don't underestimate me,
a Navy HQ vice admiral!

1444
01:37:01,690 --> 01:37:02,900
Drop dead!

1445
01:37:08,870 --> 01:37:12,700
You're very tough as I thought
but far from the best condition.

1446
01:37:12,700 --> 01:37:15,430
I'll bury you with my Haki!

1447
01:37:15,790 --> 01:37:19,460
I don't mind that you hate pirates.
You belong to the Navy after all.

1448
01:37:19,460 --> 01:37:22,420
But I won't let you touch my friends!

1449
01:37:22,420 --> 01:37:25,780
I'm gonna continue the adventure with them!

1450
01:37:27,050 --> 01:37:30,720
I'm tired of having a fruitless conversation.

1451
01:37:30,720 --> 01:37:33,520
Let's settle this!

1452
01:37:42,610 --> 01:37:43,420
What?!

1453
01:37:45,320 --> 01:37:47,930
Gum-Gum...

1454
01:37:49,450 --> 01:37:51,970
...Red Hawk!

1455
01:38:09,470 --> 01:38:10,590
He did it!

1456
01:38:10,590 --> 01:38:12,760
--Hey, let's get to the ship!
--Yeah!

1457
01:38:12,760 --> 01:38:14,770
--Hurry up!
--O-Okay!

1458
01:38:14,770 --> 01:38:17,450
Boss! Run!

1459
01:38:19,770 --> 01:38:20,920
You...

1460
01:38:22,560 --> 01:38:24,040
Pirate...

1461
01:38:25,570 --> 01:38:27,400
Defeat...

1462
01:38:29,030 --> 01:38:31,450
Hey, we left Straw Hat behind.

1463
01:38:31,450 --> 01:38:33,990
Don't worry! He'll be here any minute.

1464
01:38:33,990 --> 01:38:36,500
The problem is the warships on standby.

1465
01:38:36,500 --> 01:38:39,670
It's best if we can get away
by the Coup de Burst but...

1466
01:38:39,670 --> 01:38:42,330
We already used it on our way here.

1467
01:38:42,330 --> 01:38:45,070
--Oh, then, there is no problem!
--What?

1468
01:38:45,960 --> 01:38:48,050
We brought them from the base!

1469
01:38:48,050 --> 01:38:50,180
When did you get here?

1470
01:38:51,760 --> 01:38:53,510
All we gotta do is wait for Luffy...

1471
01:38:53,510 --> 01:38:54,870
He's here.

1472
01:39:10,700 --> 01:39:12,740
Alright, set sail!

1473
01:39:17,450 --> 01:39:18,520
I see.

1474
01:39:18,910 --> 01:39:20,370
What about Komei and the others?

1475
01:39:20,370 --> 01:39:24,500
<i>We brought all of them on board the warship
that was on standby. The vice admiral, too.</i>

1476
01:39:24,500 --> 01:39:27,670
--Okay. Thank you for your trouble.
--<i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

1477
01:39:27,670 --> 01:39:28,880
Clank.

1478
01:39:29,380 --> 01:39:33,050
He pushed them quite far. What a shame.

1479
01:39:33,050 --> 01:39:36,200
Your grandson always gets in our way.

1480
01:39:38,390 --> 01:39:43,310
Even in this era of the contest of strength,
if you have ingenuity, you can compete.

1481
01:39:43,310 --> 01:39:47,150
Komei said he wants to prove it
to all the people in the world.

1482
01:39:47,150 --> 01:39:53,380
Oh, it's him! I remember thinking
"He's so spindly. Will he be okay?"

1483
01:39:53,950 --> 01:39:58,350
I'm newly assigned! I'm Corporal Komei!

1484
01:40:00,080 --> 01:40:03,920
His belief in not wanting to
depend on Devil Fruits.

1485
01:40:03,920 --> 01:40:06,130
I sort of like it.

1486
01:40:06,130 --> 01:40:10,780
Don't worry! He won't break down
because he lost this time! He's not that wimpy!

1487
01:40:13,630 --> 01:40:16,390
Stop laughing without a care in the world.

1488
01:40:19,140 --> 01:40:22,520
It's all rebuilt.
What will you do about the ship?

1489
01:40:22,520 --> 01:40:28,770
We'll sail it. Even though they touched it.
That guy Dojaku didn't cut corners at least.

1490
01:40:28,770 --> 01:40:32,300
Yeah? Well,
that ship is cool so that's good.

1491
01:40:32,320 --> 01:40:38,640
The most important thing for me is them
and we took back the next most important thing, too.

1492
01:40:41,950 --> 01:40:44,810
Oh, the Jolly Roger that I drew!

1493
01:40:44,870 --> 01:40:52,010
FOX

1494
01:40:45,170 --> 01:40:49,040
I didn't even wanna look at
this annoying symbol but...

1495
01:40:49,040 --> 01:40:52,010
...I'm starting to feel this isn't so bad.

1496
01:40:52,340 --> 01:40:56,130
Feels like we can't call ourselves
the Foxy Pirates without it.

1497
01:40:56,130 --> 01:40:59,850
I see! I feel happy
when someone appreciates what I did.

1498
01:41:01,520 --> 01:41:03,890
Thank you for fighting with me.

1499
01:41:09,360 --> 01:41:12,190
But the temporary cease-fire ends now!

1500
01:41:12,900 --> 01:41:16,490
From this moment on,
we're each other's enemy again!

1501
